alford.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 How many years did you live here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 There? Well - we were very old neighbours there - they lived - I got - left there got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15881451 
Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433  when I was nearly twenty-six and went to live in - Broughten but I think they'd been in - lived in there from being }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15881451 Married}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433  and that'd be - suppose - getting round twenty years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you move to anywhere after this before you were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15881451 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did I live anywhere? I didn't live - I left {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Salford{\*\xmlclose}
 when my first son was born. My wife had a nervous breakdown and then went to live at Gorton for twelve months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did your parents live anywhere else though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No, me - me parents died in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Ashton Street{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose}. It was - they both died at the same age, my mother and father. But - my father was a year older but my mother died - lived a year after him you see, and they were sixty-eight and a half when they died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Your mother was forty when you were born and your father was forty-one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Do you know where your father came from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 He came from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Salford{\*\xmlclose} - he was born in Salford.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What was his occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Iron dresser. A fetler. It's not a - an highly skilled thing but it's not a labouring it's just in between - iron dresser.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did he ever have another job before or after that or was he always an iron dresser?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Oh - he left - he retired when he was sixty - he lost an eye. Now today he would have got compensation for that, he didn't get a penny and there was no old age pensions for them - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did he do any casual or part time jobs at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Me father? He never went out, only to work and back. He used - he went to church until - when he was a young man}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6767433  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 a heart attack and they never went to church after but very strict man. But - strict in his own way - he couldn't read or wri
te but - they had to read to him so when it came to my turn I said I'm not doing it. I wouldn't do it - I refused to read - stop in and read - but my sister, Janey was a bit of a slave - so it happened I thought not fall for that. Well I was - I don't kno
w a bit more progressive or what but - I was not star at school - I wasn't - arithmetic that was my star turn - our school - our old schoolmaster was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Do you ever remember your father being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh he was out of work once or twice. There was a long }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3242559\charrsid6767433 engineers}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
 strike - oh, it was a very long one. And he - he used to occasionally get fed up with the job and he purposely used to stop off and have a bit of a boose and get the sack. And then he'd - sometime getting a job. I remember three jobs 
that he was in for a long time. The Burghs, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}St Simon Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, Strangeways.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Is that a Dutch firm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Deburghs - no it was - I don't think so. Well it was a well known foundry in those days. {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Jacksons{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} - somewhere off {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Oldfield Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} and Robinsons, 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Springfield Lane{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} - these are the three that I - he spent most of his life - he was a long time at - Robinsons at the finish.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 And always doing the same job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh yes, he never did anything else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Where did your mother come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Salford.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Had she any jobs before she was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15881451 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 She worked in the mill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What was she in the mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Oh I couldn't tell - weaver I think - I don't know, I'm only guessing. And she worked until several of the children were born and they - I noticed th
at while she was working the children died. Now after, when she stopped working they started to live and - Pooly died of course and Lisa died when she was twenty-five but the three first -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Do you remember what hours she did in the mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No idea. No idea at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Who looked after the children while your mother was at work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No idea of that. I know nothing about that early - I'm - I'm guessing a lot of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 How many rooms did you have in this house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Two up and two down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did anyone else besides your parents or brothers and sisters ever live in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Yes, me grandfather. He was ninety-six. I can only just remember him - he was a little fat old man used to sit - we had a big chest of drawers it was only - it wasn't 
a big kitchen and there was the family and the old man used to - I can must remember him sat there a little fat old man and then he went to his daughter's at Burnley. He was ninety-six when he died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 So he lived with you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Yes - He was Ir - he come from Ireland.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did your mother ever have any paid help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No. We didn't have any help at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 She did it all herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 She was a marvel. She couldn't read or write - she - she was - I'm saying it and I mean it - she was a 
wonderful woman. She wasn't - she couldn't read or write but she was a good woman and - the neighbours was a pretty tough neighbourhood and - the people in trouble, it didn't matter how bad they were, she'd go and try to help 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did she do her washing at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh did all the wash - she used to do all her washing and - there was only a little table and how she got through it is a mystery to me.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did she make any clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No, I never knew her to make anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Were the clothes you had new or secondhand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well, we got them new but didn't get 'em often. No, no secondhand clothes - didn't have secondhand clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Do you remember where your clothes were bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Yes, I do. I'm trying - now this - he was a Jew. What was he - on {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Blackfriars Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
, he was a French Jew - what was his name. Used to get my clothes there I know. I don't know where my father got his. I don't know where my mother got her's but I know they used to take me there. I don't know his name - I couldn't tell you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 When were they bought - any special time of the year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10115462\charrsid6767433 Round about Whit week. Oh!}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
 they used to scrape up a suit of - a new suit of sort. They - they know me mother. She used to raise the wind a bit with a spare time job - They used to sell clothes on the flat -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Your mother did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well - no, she didn't sell clothes but she went and bought some and then used to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 On the flat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Flat iron market. And she used to make - them into parcels and I think somebody took 'em for 'em a
nd - took them and pawned them for her and she made a bit out - of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Who was this who used to sell on the market?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 The same man that - she used to get the clothes off. Alf Hertsog - he was name Hetsog. Alf - she used to buy things off him that 
he bought for auction and - string them up and somebody in the neighbourhood - a woman used to take them to the pawnshop and my mother used to make something out of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did your mother or father ever repair your shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh, I never knew my father to repair them. Nor my mother - I couldn't say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Do you remember when these were bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
When you needed 'em badly I think. No, I don't know - there was no given date. Me father used to have - funny story about his shoes. Very heavy shoes and he
 worked in the - foundry - they worked in a foundry. Used to chip the - what the moulders did - made the mess of the moulds they chipped the rough stuff off it and they called that an iron dresser fetler - that was his job. And when he'd done with them fo
r
 used in the foundry he used to cut the tope off and those were his slippers. When I wanted chastising he used to call me over and say turn round and he was giant - he - had a thinnish face and my daughters very like him in appearance, that's her behind y
o
u, and he used to hit you on the back with this shoe and it'd knock you across the kitchen - if you didn't fall you was lucky. So - and - oh, he was a character. Very strict man, he used to swear a bit and - you weren't to swear though, oh no, but - you h
adn't to do anything, only what you should do and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did he help your mother in the house at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
He didn't help anybody - he was a bit of a nuisance to me mother. During this - as we go along you'll come to some funny tricks of me father's.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did he dress you, undress you, bath you - do anything like that to help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
No. And then - and bath me - no, he - a lad hadn't to do anything. We had flag floors and - oh we mustn't clean the flour and - they're not going to make a woman - girl of my lad - that was his idea. Ig - Ignorance really. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 He never read to you either?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Anyway I took no notice of him - I used to help my mother. But one day, just before he came home on Saturday I knocked the bucket over after doing it. So, oh, me mother and me was - I was for it and all if I did it and me mother. I took no notice of him.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did he ever read to you or tell you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No, read to me - he couldn't read. No, he couldn't read.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did he take you out of all without your mother or look after you while she was out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
He used to take me sometimes out - it was generally when he was on the boose - he used to take me along the market and buy me some ice cream and he used to buy oyster - oh aye - for himself - he'd a few - he - he
 wasn't exactly selfish but he'd have a few oysters and - took me to Warrington once or twice to a sister of his. But - I don't remember him ever doing - he was - he was a good father in a way - a strict father but he wasn't a loving father. Didn't make a
 fuss of you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you have jobs to do to help your mother or father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh I - I did everything I could to help me mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you help your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well, I couldn't help him much. I was - well, no, I didn't, I hadn't much time. I worked and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I mean when you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
I didn't help much, me father - he wouldn't let me help - he wouldn't - a lad had to be a lad - he hadn't to do anything only just go to school and - like hold his own. Then - this is another thing - I was a
lter boy. My mother was pretty religious - he went himself until he took bad as I said but - I never - didn't play in Greengate. My school }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3242559\charrsid6767433 pals}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433  lived in Broughton so I used to go to Broughton. So they used to think I was stuck up and some of 'em -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Was Broughton a better district?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Oh better then, yes. But - oh, much better. But - I had to fight my way through the - like - now, if I got a good hiding outside he'd give me another one for getting a good hiding. So I had to fight hard to get out - of it - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did the older children help the younger children at all - helping them get dressed?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10115462\charrsid6767433 Lisa}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433  - I was her pet but she used to knock me about like a bit. She - was ill and it - they used to wear corsets you know and it had to be lac
ed tight. Well, I had to lace her - corsets but if anybody said a word about me, oh, they - they - she wouldn't let anybody say a word about me but me mother and I perhaps me father hadn't hit me for some time or me mother - never hit me - but Lisa'd belt
 me. But - she used to take me in hand before to take - no, she made a fuss of me. And I had to tighten her corsets and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 So the younger ones helped the older ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 But - nobody had to touch me only her. But we - of course she couldn't stop me fa
ther but she didn't like it - and if - if anybody said anything against me - she told 'em off. Yes. Beautiful looking woman. And she had red cheeks when she was dead. I've never seen that in a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3242559\charrsid6767433 corpus}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433  in my life. Beautiful looking woman she was. Twenty-five - had beautiful black curly hair. Sheer black.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time on schooldays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No, they wasn't too strict about that. I hadn't to be out. I had to be in. I hadn't to be out after a given time - I had to be in. an
d a brother - a pal of mine and me used to go to Craven Moor on Sunday morning and - I had to be back opening time to go for beer for him. And, I'll tell you all about the beer as we come to it later - go on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Who put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh, I put myself to bed from a fairly early age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 You don't remember the age?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
No. I can remember one thing that - I've laughed all me life about it - you know, in - until a child comes to the age of reason at the age of seven years. I remember going to bed on th
e night of me seventh birthday with a heavy heart. I could commit sin then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you share the bedroom or bed with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 With my brother before he was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15881451 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Just the two of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 You only had two bedrooms - how did you manage to sleep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Well me brother and me was on this side - me father and mother was on that side and me sisters was in the other room. That - that's all that was living that I remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What room did you bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh, a big tin bath.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 In front of the fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 How often did you bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh pretty - pretty regular. Mother kept us clean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 How about clean clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh very regular change them. Very regular. Oh she was very good at that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Not just once a week?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Where did the family have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 We had them to a regular time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 In which room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
In the living room. The door, and there was just a partition, then you was in the house. And there was a table just round - inside the partition - me father's chair on the other side and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3242559\charrsid6767433 daren
\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433  sit in his chair never mind anything else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 You all had your own places did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh yes, yes. You sat in the same place. I sat nearest door.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did they ever }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10115462\charrsid6767433 eat}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433  in another room for special occasions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 It was the back scullery the next one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Where did your mother - cook - in the back scullery?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
No, she cooked on the fire - I don't know how she managed it. She was a - she was a good cook and all. And - she had to do it on small money too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What time did you have breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh, I couldn't - I don't remember - but it must have been fairly early because I was always in good time fore school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you all have breakfast together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No, I - I can't remember that. I think he 
had his break - he went to work early - he went to work at six and he had his breakfast first and went. Me mother used to get up for him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did he take sandwiches or something with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 He didn't take sandwiches - he used to come home to his meals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Do you remember what you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I don't remember where he worked in - off {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Oldfield Road
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. Oh - Deburghs - now wait a - I said Deburghs didn't I. It was Muhlers. Muhlers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Do you remember what you had for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Not - not much. There
 used to be a - we had something - there used to be a herring curers and - my mother used to send me - the sister that died she liked red herrings - not in my line at all - and this herring curer, you could go and get a bundle for threepence. You could ge
t a basin of cracked eggs for a few coppers. So I used to go for that and - it'd probably be cracked eggs that I had. But I wouldn't have nothing to do with - red herrings - I didn't want to go for them but Lisa - you go - and that was an order.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What did you have on Sunday - anything special?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh always meat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 For breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh no, I think we had a bit of bacon on - Sunday - I'm not sure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What about dinners during the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh always had meat. But when I say always, no, a chick
en - you'll come to the chicken stunt in a minute - perhaps - is it now the food stuff. Oh all right. Well there used to be a - what they called Chicken Ann - and she used to come round with a push cart on Saturday and me mother used to get a chicken for 
a
 shilling. And - she could make a good meal of it and - first she used to make the broth - she used to bake and all - she could bake - and how she did it all is a mystery but - as soon as this chicken broth was ready I was called in and had a bowl of chic
k
en broth. She fed me all right. Had to go to different butchers for threepenn'orth - sixpenn'roth of pieces - she used to make stews with dumplings in and - they were all right. Barley broth. Sheep's head broth and - I always been fond - I am yet - I made
 - my wife used to make me sheeps head but I'm not as success with them - potted meat. I do a chicken - how she - but -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you have something special for Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh we always had meat of some sort.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What about teas - what did you have for a tea meal during the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Tomatoes I think - yes, tomatoes and a little cake I think. And - course when the children started working that helped - like me father never got a lot of money but - and he'd always want - he didn't keep too much but he ke
pt some. And he retired when he was sixty and after his six was finished there was nothing only four shillings from the - he was a life member of the Odd Fellows and had four shillings for a life member. Pension like. Kept that for himself. And - this is 
true - I used to - I was out of me time by this time like and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16152710\charrsid6767433 me}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2822130\charrsid6767433 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433  Jimmy was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 It was a dressed up job was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well he was at - a gown moulder - it was hard job but they got the money. I think me father got twenty-four shillings and Jimmy got abo
ut two pound.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Jimmy was your father's friend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Well - yes. He used to visit - this is what's a funny part coming to me. Now I was a tall strippling. I was never weak - I was sturdy and strong and light - but I wasn't heavy - I was under ten stone
 and - I had a pair of tight fitting trousers and Jimmy was a little fat man. So - I - I was careless with me clothes - I used to throw them. Mother used to put them away. My wife did the same - she put them away and now I have to put them away. But - I'm
 
not so good at it yet. Anyway - h - wouldn't ask me for these trousers - he said ask him for those trousers - he doesn't use them. So it made me laugh. So - I said - what, Jimmy those trousers - are you joking. He never joked. Joking - I'm not. Said Jimmy
 
can't get in them. He said he'll get in them if you give 'em him. Well, I rather liked old Jimmy, he was a nice old fellow. So I said right-o. Well I saw Jimmy with these trousers on. And one foot, one foot, one foot, one foot and when he wanted to get th
em off he had to send for his son to pull 'em off. Well, that didn't - the finish of the food and Jimmy. Me mother didn't get a bit of meat big enough to give Jimmy a bit - he was earning no money mind you - and if I didn't give Jimmy a threepe}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16152710\charrsid6767433 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 ny tip - me 
mother used to - he used to leg me mother. And if I didn't give Jimmy his spends before I paid me mother me - wages like -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What did Jimmy do to earn this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Jimmy did nothing - he was a poor old fellow that fell on a bad time and his son was no go
od and he lived in a room - he was having an awful -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 He had been a moulder?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Yes, but he'd lost the use of his hands - he was a nice old man I - I rather liked him. But he used to - fuss the missus - he used to annoy her when I wasn't there - the
re was only we that'd tackle him. At the finish I told him to behave himself. But - you might think I'm telling lies but I'm not. He used to - compel me to keep me mother out of trouble to give Jimmy threepence. I had to give his - his spends ninepence be
f
ore me mother got her wages. And then I had to pay me lodgings like and - was a rather dressy young fellow like and - doing a bit of courting later on and - anyway at the finish I told him, I said, now you've gone far enough. I heard him going on to my si
ster - the one, Janey - who he used to terror - terrify her.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did your mother bake her own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Make her own bread? Yes, she baked her -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did she make jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I don't remember - I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did she bottle fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Wait a minute - she made - she did something. She did - she bottle something. Couldn't say now what it was - I was only young. I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did she make pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 She - she - she baked her own bread - she might have made jam - I don't know - I - I couldn't swear to it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did she make pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Yes, she did pickle things. Yes, she did that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What about wine or medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 She didn't do anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did she make any beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did your father or mother grow their own vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 We'd nowhere to grow them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did they by any fruit and vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Yes. Yes. Used to buy them. Well they were cheep in those days, very cheap.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did they have tinned or dried vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh - dried - vegetables - no tinned stuff. I don't remember any tinned stuff at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 They couldn't keep hens or pigs or goats could they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 When I was about twelve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Where did you keep it then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 In the yard. I had to get rid of it. Oh it w
as - it was a dirty thing. It was - used to tick the kids - my sister that died her young man - he was no damned good, it was a good job she did die, he was no good - clever workman but wouldn't work - but anyway she died. Good job to get out of his way i
n a way. But he bought this nanny goat and I had it 'til it - me mother was always complaining of the dirt. And I - I don't know how I got rid of it. Oh I do, I sold it to a - a - at the pub.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Where did he take it to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 It was - they - they kept a p
ub and they were named Spong, I remember then well because our children were - with one of the sons later in life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 How many times a week did you have meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Meat. Oh fairly often. I used to go for pieces.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you ever have tinned meat?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Tinned meat? No, never. Never saw - I don't think I ever saw tinned anything in our house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you ever get extra meat such as rabbit from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Rabbits? Yes, we used -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 From poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No, not from - you could - nowhere to poach.
 No, the way it used to be though its - when I first came here where the school is there was rabbits.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Do you remember seeing your mother having less food so the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Left food - no. Oh no, no, he wouldn't like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did she ever go short?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Nobody ever went short - no, no. She was a - she was a good - she was a good eater. She used to bake a lot and she - as soon as the ban cakes were ready she used to call me on - in - and while they were hot put - I don't know whethe
r it was butter or - oh, we were supposed to have butter I know - no margarine for his - mind you he didn't buy it - he - he was out of work but no margarine, but we used to have it. I knew that but - didn't let on to him. He didn't know it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did he have more food than the rest of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No. He didn't want more. Oh no, he was fair like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Were you allowed to talk during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Could hardly breathe.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Were they strict at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Strict? He was a terribly strict man an
d although he was an ignorant man most of it was for your good when you come to examine it. But he was - he was a bit of a savage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Were you allowed to choose what you wanted on the table or did you have to have what you were given?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 There wasn't much to choose from - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you have to clean the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Oh well, they got cleaned - I don't know they had to - they did get cleaned. I don't think so - I don't remember anything being left. Me mother was a very good cook - it was marvelous wh
at she could do and I used to go to the different butchers for different - Kents, Bol - Bowshers, little butchers like - they know me for going and all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 If you wanted the salt did you ask someone to pass it or did you wait 'til if was passed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh we asked for - it was all right to ask for anything we want.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Could you ask - for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Yes. Oh yes. Duplings I was very fond of and - I - I used to often ask for dumplings - more dumplings.
