 used to manage something special. That would come to food again. This is some more that's true that's extraordinary about him. We used to have a draw out at Finnigans the leather people for the - thirty-eight years and a half. I went there before I was t
hirteen and left when I was fifty-one and a half. They took the firm and I was in the window civic week showing how to make trunks and when I was doing the window I didn't do in work - girls did it by this time - machines do it now. And I won -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Christmas draw?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Finnigans - in the works we used to have a Christmas draw and I was very lucky. I won seven - nine prizes in seven years and they used to call it Billy Finns draw. So, anyway one year I won three prizes. A bottle of run - a leg of lamb and a }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14040315\charrsid6767433 turkey}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
. So I went home and put them down like and he picked the run up and took it away. So I said, where you taking that? He said, I'm putting it away. He - my father did. I looked at him. Before that I used to have a drink and - that Christmas I think I
'd had one or two and I wasn't so good so I said I' - have a drop of run. He said, you wasn't. I said, I what? I brought a bottle - I won it. He said, did you? I said when you put that bottle of rum on there it was mine he said and any more that you put t
h
ere is mine and all. Well I had to let him get away with it for peace for me mother. Well I said give me mother a drop. He said, it's no good for your mother. True. So, I said, right, you'll never see another bottle of rum if I win it - I said you'll get 
none, never mind me. I'll see to you. Any way he wouldn't give me none. And it - that's true.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you have any musical instruments in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 None at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did anyone sing in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I don't think so - I don't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 You never made music at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Me mother used to just - no, I wouldn't call 'em - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did your parents play any games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Never knew - never knew him to play a game in his life of any sort.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Nor your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No, well, I don't think - I don't remember. I didn't spend a lot of time in the house - he was too tough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Were there any books in the house?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Books? No, I don't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What about newspapers or magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 It was newspapers - I don't re
member magazines. They - my daughter had to read everything to him - my sister rather - I tell you they was read as they come along but I wouldn't have none.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you say your mother could read?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No, nor write - neither of them. But may father was
 very good with figures, he was, and me mother wasn't bad - they could both - manage to count without any trouble.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Do you remember a funeral in the family when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Funerals? I only remember one funeral - no, two funerals. Liza's and Polly's.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Who attended it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
There must have been another one between Liza and Tom. I don't remember - I can't remember clearly. I was the - I was the baby of the family see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 You don't remember any funeral at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I remember Polly's the one that died when she was eight - I was six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you go to it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Yes. And I remember Liza dying - I was twelve. And I went to that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Do you remember what sort of clothes the mourners wore?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh we had black.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 All of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Far as I remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Were you ever taken out visiting neighbours, friends or relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
He never took me only to - he took me one time to a friend somewhere in Manchester and the lad hit me - the lad of the house so I hit him and hit him hard. And
 he - he run crying to his mother. So - hit your father's friends do you. I said well he hit me what did I do? Said hit him back of course. I said have done, so they nearly had a row.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Were you ever taken just shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No. I used to go errands for me mother. Oh, I used to do all her errands.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you ever go out with your father on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well me - as I told you he took me round town when he was on the booze. Used to buy me an }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14040315\charrsid6767433 ice cream}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433  and a black pudding perhaps and - and he'd have some }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14040315\charrsid6767433 oysters}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 That was the only time he took you out? Did you ever go out for outings with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Never went on a picnic with either of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you go away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No, never. The first time I saw the sea was a friend 
of ours give me two tickets to go to Southport and - a pal of mine in the street, we went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Southport{\*\xmlclose}
 on these two tickets and it was from a place in Whit Lea - Lane - afterwards became a cinema. I can remember going from there. I don't remember much about that but - I was only I was only young - perhaps ten or eleven I think.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 So you never went on holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh, I never went on holiday - no. Holidays I had was when I joined the Terriers - camp. I joined - and I did thirty-eight years in that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What did you do on Saturdays and Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well I used to go and watch football.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 On Saturday as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Yes. And go dancing at night. Oh I - I used to to a lot of dancing. I used to dance with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What did you do as a child though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
A child? Oh, I don't remember what I did - I went to Salford - I went to Salford when I was very young but I don't remember anything but that - Salford football and I used to get the football and read that - if I had money enough - but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What did you do on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Sundays, oh aye, church. I used to go to church morning and Benediction at night. Sunday school in the afternoon. Oh good lad. Good lad to be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you wear different clothes to go to church on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No, I - I wore me Sun
day clothes - I generally used to have some clothes that was a bit better. And of course I had - you have a - a smock and a cassock and smock like - I forget the name of it now - white on black like - on the alter - oh aye, I used to have a sleep now and 
then there too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you play games on Sunday - were you allowed to play games or work at home on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I did but they didn't - no, I used to go to Broughton and if there was a game on I was in it. But - they didn't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 You were telling me about this schoolmaster?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
It was after I'd left the alter but I'd been to Benediction and I was going to Broughton to meet my pals. So - old Mr O'Neill came along and he was with his son and his son was named Hughie - a man schoolmaster - six foot f
our he was, Hughie. So he said - smart young man William. I said thank you Sir. Said, you tot to thank me for that. I said, have I? Said yes, I made you into a man. He reckoned he knocked it into me. So he still locked at me. I said, you didn't spare the 
c
ane much. He said, you deserved it. So I said, all right, never mind. He said, I've made you into a good man. So - he'd knocked it into me he said but he was an old villain - they used to - ooh used - used - that was a joke you know, he'd send me with an 
e
rrand to his wife, come back and then he'd give me the cane for some trivial thing that I'd done before I went and oh, this cane, he couldn't half hurt you. He - he caught no one time, in school, I was only good at mental arithmetic - I used to dodge all 
t
he other when I could and anyway we were having geography and he turned round and where was that? I didn't know so I give a guess - wrong of course. So of course I was for it for that. Another time - geography - they - the best scholar in the school - Bil
l
y Duffy - I used to get him near me see so he could give me a lift if I was - if I was stuck in things like - a terrible speller I am yet. Anyway - I never failed - I always managed to get through, but - Billy Duffy's on the other side of the group and I 
h
ad a peashooter - I blow a pea and it hit him in the eye and he said oh. Oh I didn't have get belted for that. All this is true. But they - the old fellow - the old schoolmaster - he had red whiskers. Yes. He said he made a man out of me - he might have d
one I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did your parents attend church?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Me mother always attended.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 How often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh every Sunday. Come confession and communion.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What about your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh, he never went after he was sick. He - he collapsed with hea
rt trouble and they told him he must not go upstairs - mustn't go up - mustn't climb up stairs - he mustn't drink beer or tea. Well he always went upstairs and if he couldn't get beer he drank tea. He - he didn't go to church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you ever go on any Sunday school outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Well, have to walk it. Used to go to Curson Wall and walked it and got buns and milk. That was the Sunday out - that was the Sunday school outing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What other church social activities did you take part in - you were an alter boy but were you in the choir too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
No, there was nothing - nothing uplifting in those days. It was a very old school and - it was antique school and antique methods and - anyway - they turned out some wonderful scholars.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you have any clubs at church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
They had club. Wasn't successful. They started that - they started that club through me and - but it was after I left school - it was when I was a man. I came home from the war - I said I'd like to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 But you never went to a club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No, I am not a club man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you say grace at meals at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I can't say - I don't remember - I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did they say family prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Who taught you to say your prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh me mother taught me
 to say me prayers. I never missed me prayers. Oh, they taught you at school and all. Religious education in Catholic Schools you know. I - I was - I tell you - a boy comes to the age - age of reason at seven years I went upstairs with leaden feet that ni
ght - I'd come to the age of not going to heaven kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Do you remember any of the celebrations at church - any of the festivals as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 They used to have missions and they used to have wonderful preachers. And - I am yet interested in sermons. I used to go to 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}St Mary's Mulberry Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} - that up - wonderful church up here, the new one you know, beautiful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 When you were a child do you remember any of the celebrations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I was never in charge of any celebrations.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 You don't remember any of the festivities at church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No, beyond missions I don't remember anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did your father take an interest in politics?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well he said he was a Liberal - I don't think he knew anything about it. I - I'm - I used to think I w
as Labour and I - I was. Labour used to be unfairly treated. But today I'm not Labour because I don't believe it is Labour. I think it's more Socialism and Communism - nearer to that than Labour and - well it's a menace to the country in my opinion.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Do you know why your father was Liberal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Why? Well he said Gladsons was a good man and Disra}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16152710\charrsid6767433 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 li was the opposite and that's about all he knew I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did your mother take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh I think she voted like him. No, I - I don't think either of them knew anything about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Do you remember them voting before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 1918? Oh he always voted Liberal me father. I've never voted Liberal. Never in my life. I vote Conservative.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 They do say that in those days some man r
isked losing their job or their house if they voted differently from the people that employed them. Do you know if your father felt he had to vote for a certain person because of the people he worked for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I don't think the people he worked for had anything to do with houses in his day.
