lked up to him and - go on, he said, lad him on to the police station. So he was that tought that Tracey was having nothing to do with him. And told you - did I tell you that I saw another criminal drop dead out of a pub - did I tell you that. Another day
 - I'd been - Paddy Belman - he was a villain. He'd been - he - a criminal he used to a - - he was only a little sturdy fellow but he used to - attack people and stab them and rob them. And - he lived - he lived off Greengate, down - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15881451 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433  to a fine young
 woman and I was coming home from work and I saw this fellow - I'd had a bit of a truckle with him once, I was glad that he was - they'd got rid of him, anyway I won't say I was glad he was dead but I didn't know he was dead but he fell out and fell on th
e
 floor. And the police were soon there and he was dead all right. Doctor come, he was dead, shot through the heart. Now what had happened - the publican said that he'd raised - got a stool up to hit him and this revolver - well he might have done I don't 
know. But there was one of the Tracey's girls mixed up with him in the pub in that. But - oh, he was a villain was Belman. But - he fell out and fell on the floor dead.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Do you remember much about the police in Greengate - how you felt about them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well I didn't like them. I used to feel sorry for them in a way but I didn't admire them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Why did you feel sorry for the police?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 For the police? Oh, well I - the police - oh I did - they were brutes. I thought you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16152710\charrsid6767433 mea}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 nt the criminals. I didn't feel - I felt sorry for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Why did you feel sorry for the criminals and not the police?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Well, I felt sorry for them both in a way. The criminals used to attack the police perhaps but the police used to murder the criminals and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 They were very bad with them were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
There - there was one they called Good Advice - a big fat man named Lane. And - he was always giving them good advice. Well they used to make a fool of him all the time so the good advice was no use - the abuse was a l
ot of use. There was one they called - they called him Navvy Jack.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 This was a policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Police - Policeman - Navvy - they called him Navvy Jack - he was a big hulking fellow and - I forget his number but I know the policeman that took on - over
 after him but one of the toughs of Greengate pulled the grid up and that knocked his helmet fast down ever his face. He went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}America{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 and because quite a prominent person. A mason in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}America{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. His Uncle told me about that. Micky Marley and - after his -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 How do you think the police treated the ordinary people, not the criminals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 This was a criminal - he was no - no rough. He was a scuttler kind of business before he went to America.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What about the scufflers - did you have them in Greengate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Scufflers - oh they used to go - gangs used to meet and fire bottles at one another and belts with buckles on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 They were called scuttlers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well, they called them scuttlers. There I there was the Adelphi gang - Red Shelly was the leader o
f them and Johnny Hoddy was the leader of the Greengate mob - the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Queen Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} it was - the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Queen Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} mob and the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Queen Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} - the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Queen Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} mob anybody could have blow him down with a feather. He was only the leader because he was - happened to be the eldest amongst them kind of business - }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15881451 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433  to quite a nice girl but he died and - she got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15881451 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433  again. But he - they never worked. Red Shelly was a villain.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did the scuttlers ever work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I don't think they worked much. There was one fe
llow, Skerry Nob they called him - he was known for fighting - he used to work but he was one of 'em but he used to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What about the ordinary people in greengate - how did the police behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh all right. If - if it - as a matter of fact if you was all right they protected you. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Were you afraid of the police?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Now me - I don't - no, I wasn't a friend of them, I wasn't an enemy of 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Were you afraid of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No, I couldn't say I was afraid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did your mother ever threaten you with them - say I'll bring a policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Oh no. I'd have liked to have been a policeman I thought when I was younger - but I'm glad I wasn't. They did some dirty work. I knew quite a lot of police as I got older. In the military part of the world - in Salford.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 You remember the Sien Fein trouble do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Yes I remember that well, ginger was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 You would see it down Greengate - this was the Irish area wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I - I don't know much about them only Ginger was - used go with a - gang that went after them, you know - he was brave Ginger. And -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Who were the gang that went after the Sein Feins?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Yes. He was an ex Captain in the Army - rose from the ranks. He got - he got his pension, he used to say I'l
l never got a pension. He used to go looking for boose all the time. And he used to come where I was in and I've seen him drunk and absolutely drunk in the barracks in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}
Cross Lane{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. And when he went to get on duty they had to put him in a cell. Told me that himself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 And he was a policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
And he was a policeman - he'd go on duty and they'd put him in a cell to sleep it off. But he was a brave man and he was a good man. He was afraid of nothing. He'd tackle anything. And the - the tough characters 
didn't fancy him like when he went after 'em. I - I've talked to him since he retired but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you belong to a youth organization while you were young?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 None at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No. No. I joined the terriers when I was young and that was my interest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 How old would you be when you joined the Terriers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Nineteen. And I didn't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 That would we what year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 The third B.B.L.F. I joined - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Cross Lane{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose}. And I left. The Eighth Lanashire Fusiliers at Broughton. But in 1916 I was transferred from - it became the Seventh and they in - in 1908 - there's a photo somewhere of me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 You say you got the Military Medal - which war did you get it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I got it - I got it - when I come home, they sent it after me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Which war was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
1914 - 18. Here - here this is funny about the Military Medal. You know, don't put this on it there. Very little store on it because I've seen people do wonderful things and get nothing. But somebody must have thought I did something but I wouldn't have 
got that. Those medals have gone to my clever grandson - this is the clever one. My mother and father were - well, they were poor. And they had rather hard times. We never starved - were never hungry and we always had clothes of a certain - well, we alway
s had a bit something different for Sunday. They were strict - me father was very strict - me mother was a gentle lovely old lady - lovely old lady. A wonderful woman, could do - she could do - she did do everything - anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 And worked and had a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Yes. Nine children. And never grumbeled. And she used to have a funny idea about children. I put this down to simplicity myself - to a certain extent. She said God never sends a mouth without food for it. And anybody - didn't matter how bad they
 were - in distress, just near us, no used in telling her they were bad, she'd go to try to help 'em. Oh, she'd time for that and all. She was a wonderful person she was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 But only three of the children lived to work you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Yes. Liza. Janey, Tom and me. Four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 How did you spend your spare time when you were at school, did you have hobbies or go fishing or walking or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14040315\charrsid6767433 by cycling}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I never biked in me life - the first time I tried I went over the top so I didn't try to more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you go fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No - only for jack sharps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Where did you get those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I never did went fishing properly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Where did you get your jack sharps?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Up Sheep Wood. That's the clay pits - Clayton. Sheepham Hill way. Used to go there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What are clay pits?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
They - where they'd dug for clay and it filled up with water and there's - well, the the clay - the - the - great expanses of water and they're deep some of them too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 And you used to go fishing there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Fishing for jack sharps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you go for walks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh I loved walking. I used to have a friend - not official - I never joined a walking club or anything like that - but I could -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 You used to take a dog walking did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I used - not always - I'll tell you a funny story about the last dog we had and all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 When you were young did you take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Well I used to run a bit - me father didn't believe in athletes he said they were villains. He - He'd not faith in athletes - said they were no good. And I used to play rugby a bit but I daren't let him know. And I used to run a bit and }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14040315\charrsid6767433 daren\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433  let him know. I couldn't be a runner, I couldn't be a footballer because he wouldn't let me. I - he hadn't to know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you ever go to any theatres or concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I used to go to theatre a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 When you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Yes, used - oh not when I was a child. I started going to the Tiv in Bridge - in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Peter Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} - tuppence in the gallery.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 This was when you were quite young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Yes, and I
 used to go - yes, I went young. And I - I started about fourteen that. The comedy and the gallery for threepence - matinees. The comedy - the Tiv - the Gaiety, the Gaiety was the comedy I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you go to music halls or cinemas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh, well the Tiv was a music hall. Tiveli.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What about cinemas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I've always - I went until I got the wireless - tele - I've had that some years. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did your parents give you any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Very little. They'd no -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Do you remember how much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Only - it was only coppers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Just now and again or regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I - I used to get a penny now and then I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What did you spend it on - do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh toffee.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Always on toffee?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did anyone outside the home help your mother to look after the house or family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did friends or relations help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Tell you they daren't - daren't put their nose in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 If your mother was ill or confined to bed how did she manage - when the children were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I don't know. I don't know that. I suppose the friends looked after her but I don't know - I don't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did your parents have any relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No. No - oh she had two - step-brothers but one of them was a villain. They
 were single and she used to try to help them and I had to be the medium. When my father wouldn't allow them near the house. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 How often did she see them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well, she saw them occasionally and I didn't see one of them when I knew him - he was 
no damned good - he wouldn't work - one was a nice fellow. He died from a carbuncle in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Oak{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Hospital{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose}. The other fellow, he used to - he was a clever workman but wouldn't work. He was one of the first to put tiles on pubs, you know. He wouldn't work. He had 
a stall on the flat iron market and used to look for rare coins and all that sort of thing and - he knew the value of them and take - he had - where he could - he - he got money out of it but he didn't pay towards the upkeep. The other fellow had to keep 
him - he sponged on him. So I wouldn't have nothing to do with him - Uncle Johnny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did your mother have anything to do with him at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh I don't think so - not him but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh me father - neither of them daresn't come near. They hadn't - they daresn't show their nose in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Didn't your mother and father have any friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Me mother - mother had plenty of friends. But me father only had his work friends. Old Jimmy was his pal. But the one in the tight trousers..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Where did your mother see her friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 She only saw them at - when they -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 This friend of your father's used to come and visit your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Come and visit me father regular. Saturday evening. And he was a single man, very respectable fel
low. And I used to think my word there's a difference between these two. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Where did your mother see her friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Jimmy - he - I told you he fell on evil times and lived in a ruin with him and his wife - his wife was a booter and he wasn't. 
He - he liked a drink but - he had been mind you, spent his money in drink and - he'd lived a - a drunken life I think. He had a son that had been a soldier that was no dawn good - he wouldn't work. Instead of helping 'em if he could get anything of 'em h
e'd take it. And - the father he didn't seem to want friends. He -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Where did your mother meet her friends.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh - she knew - knew them from when she was young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Where did she meet them when she wanted to see them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 She used to go into the
 - the tripe shop. My daughter - it was the son of the trips shop that my Liza that died it was her son. He was a clever engineer - he wouldn't work - he was no good. But - I'm afraid I'd have been belting him if they'd have ever got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15881451 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 When your father's friend came on Saturday night was he offered anything to eat or drink? Did he ever come to a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Who? Oh he wouldn't eat. Long as I know. No, he wouldn't have anything to eat. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 So your father and mother never had any real friends that they visited?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Not visited - no. He wouldn't let anybody come in the house. I tell you the - these very nice people they were - Mrs Dowd the publican - I'm not sure she was with them but Mrs Lee - Mrs walker were sisters - tripe shop sweets and 
tobacco - I had to go for his tobacco and - he used to - have fix with the gentry - well them and my brother were only smokers. He used to stretch it out and then call her skinny bean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 People say that in those days society was divided into different s
ocial classes or groups. What do you think the difference was in the different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well I should think our class was a respectable working man's class. But - on the poor side. We certainly weren't rich. We -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What were the other classes - do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Well - some of them were - oh - they were - what would they call them - they couldn't even keep their houses decent. There's a street next - they used to call our house - our street good husband street because they cleaned the flags. A
nd - Fleet Street the next street it was a mixture of Jews and people that lived in - spalling conditions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you see much of the Jews?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I saw quite a bit of 'em - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Was there much prejudice against the Jews in Greengate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Yes. They
 used to - when the - I've seen - fellows that used to go down putting windows - lads throw stones and break their windows when they were carrying it. I've seen that happen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Throw them at the Jews windows?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 The Jews - used to go round putting windows in some of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 You mean breaking windows?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
And - lads'd break the windows - yes. Break the windows before they were put in. And - oh, the - they - the Jews was treated rough when I were a young -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 In what way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well - - they were 
- treated badly and I saw a Jewess do something that one of our girls'd never dream of doing. One Sunday morning I was having a walk in Strangeways and the girl beautifully dressed. An old whiskered Jew come along and he dropped some money in snow. And sh
e
 was on the floor looking for the money in the snow. In her beautiful clothes. So when she got up I said - you're better than Christians they'd never do that. And they wouldn't. And - I don't think it's possible to see a Christian do it. - Anyway she did 
it - Jewess. And - I - I - I was not exactly friendly with 'em but I knew quite a few of 'em. And I didn't - I wasn't prejudiced against them. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Were they very poor as a whole, the Jews in Greengate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I don't know about - a fellow named Faulkne
r - the son used to be in charge of a group of women - Sam - the eldest son. They weren't good Jews though. The - has was in group of a batch of garment makers - they reckoned he used to earn terrific money. But they didn't live up to the Jews faith. Ther
e was a few girls - they - I don't think there was anything wrong with them but they used to be floating round town and - one }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15881451 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
 a - this is funny. The youngest one }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15881451 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433  a pork butcher. Well they don't eat pork you know. And the pork butcher got kil
led with a bomb in the first war she ran the pork shop. And I knew Sam Faulkner - he says isn't it all right Billy - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15881451 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
 to a Jew - she ran the pork shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What sort of people do you think belonged to the middle class or the upper class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well
 - I don't - middle class, tradesmen. Broughton were more of a middle class people than - Greengate was - you'd call the labouring class although there was people that were all right but mostly they were labouring - low class. Broughton were tradesman and
 - well, they were - they were higher grade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What was the difference in the homes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Oh definite different. They educated the children better. Sent them to a better school and - Greengate was a lot of - St Peter's school Greengate got a lot of peop
le from Broughton including Finnigan the Jancers. They used to - this is a bit of a blow for me now, blowing myself up - they - Mrs Finnigan -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Would you consider the Finnigans upper class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 He used - well, I suppose they were - no, be was not -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Who would you consider the upper class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No, I don't think - so.. He was - he had two daughters - they had both had club foot - they couldn't dance for nuts.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What was the difference though between the homes in - Broughton and the homes in Greengate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Oh definitely better in Broughton. I used to go in some in Broughton - oh there's a lot of little houses in Broughton but there were some just a bit better, say three up and three down and - better. I used to stay in Broughton with a friend o
f mine some time. They had a lot of lads and - mother of them was named Finn before she was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15881451 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
 so I was a pat of hers. I used to stop there. That's the lad that's on the photo with me with glasses on. His mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Who do you think were the upper classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh the upper classes they were - I suppose you class them as the shopkeepers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 You thought they were the upper class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well I suppose they were - that - that was the only upper class that I knew.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Do you ever remember being brought up to treat some people differently from others? Did you ever call some people Sir or Madam or Master?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
I always called everybody that - I thought was entitled to it, Sir. I was always civil and I don't think its out of the way myself. Some - now w
hen I went to - Layland Motors - I did twelve years there - one chap once said, I'm going to call nobody Sir. I said what's wrong with it? So he said I'm as good as anybody else. I said, you're no better are you? So he said no. I said, I don't mind callin
g anybody Sir.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did your mother and father ever teach you to touch your cap to anyone?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 To her - no, not in that way. I always saluted doctors - priests, not only the Catholic priest, any clergyman. Nuns. I've always saluted -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 How do you mean salute them - touch your cap?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Well, raise your hat or touch - yes, raise - I've always raised me hat to them. Army officers - you raise your hat to them if you know they're officers. Now in civilian they find it very awkward - they can't salute you back so all they do is just nod.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 In the district where you lived in Greengate who were the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Where I lived in Greengate? The shopkeepers - definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Always the shopkeepers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Shopkeepers - publicans were looked up to - some of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Well they - I don't know - because they took money off the people for boose - I don't know why they were looked up to but they did look up to them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 And the shopkeepers too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh, we looked up to shopkeepers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
I don't know - because they were bigger nuts than then I suppose. Let me - just before we get away from the shopkeepers. There's a pork butchers on {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Regent Road{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} now. Well - founder of that - I thought him to swim. Harry Barton. He - His grand c
hildren I think look after it now. But they - his father, they had a shop in Greengate and he was - he'd been the foreman for the Co-op years before but he was a fat old man and he snored like a pig and he - he did and I used to fill the skins with black 
puddings and the same age - I could work the machine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 When you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Yes. You go in the slaughter house. I used to do this - it was easy - I knew how to do it like - I was a pal of his and we used to go up town but he used to make pies fo
r Buaghans and places like that - big pies. Wonderful butcher and he was supposed to be a great egg. Well he died and - Harry went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}America{\*\xmlclose} and he - he }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15881451 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433  a girl off {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Broughton{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Bridge
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} and she was the first girl I ever saw on a bike in trousers. She had knickers on. Caused commotion. And harry }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15881451 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433  her and they went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}America{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} and - many years after the brother that got blow up on 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Lower Broughton Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15881451 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
 the Jewess said what's become of your Harry. Said well don't you know? Said I've no idea. Said he were only in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}America{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} a bit - he's on 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Regent Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} - been there all his life. I didn't know - I never saw him no more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 How did you come to make black puddings as a child? What did you do this for - making extra money or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I didn't make any money I just did it because I was a pal of Harry's. Oh I got nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 You actually worked in the slaughter house did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I didn't work - I was only a schoolboy - used -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 But you used to help them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well I - I thought it w
as fun for me I - I - it wasn't done for nuts - I was doing something because I wanted to do it not for what - work. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 How did you make the black puddings?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 The - the - it comes out the machine and it's a skin and the pudding - you fill it 
up and twist 'em then they're big enough. The same with a sausage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Was it a local butcher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
This was - this was Bartons pork butchers in Greengate. It was a big shop. Frankenburgs eventually took the shop up - closed the shop up. The old fellow died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 And they slaughtered their own beast and everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh aye. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Were you allowed in when that was done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I've seen them slaughter them all }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9779656\charrsid6767433 and}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433  cut - cut them up and - oh, I've seen quite a lot of that. It's all an experience. Oh I've seen a lot of things in Greengates.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Who do you think the clergy bothered with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 There's some - this is - this is not correct - it's not working right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Who do you think the teachers bothered with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Now them - socially then - oh who
 did they associate with. Oh - I don't know. I remember getting on the - Miss Magwire - I remember getting in the bus one day and she said - she'd been a teacher in the infants school - said didn't you know me, William? I said, yes, of course I know you. 
S
he said, well why - why didn't you speak? I said, should I speak? To a lady. Said, yes - you should. I started you on your way to be a man. Stanley Roman he went to be a priest. And I'd been to Finnigans dancing, come out and run into a pub to have a drin
k
 at the interval and I went in and across from where I was in the lobby I see Stanly Norman - who - down and out. He wasn't a priest he wasn't anything. He looked at - he looked like on - he saw me looking at him, he left his pint and cleared off. I - I f
ound out after that he'd been - sent away from university - studying for the priest. And he was a navy when I saw him - poor Stanley.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Who did the priests associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Freists? Only with themselves. They won't associate with anybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Do you think teachers kept to themselves to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Oh they keep to themselves. They visit one another and - priests don't go into other company much - they visit you - the priest comes here to visit me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What about doctors - and those type of people; what about farmers - did you know any farmers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Farmers? I don't know much about farmers. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What about employers who do you think they kept to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Employers? Oh I don't know. They - Finigans - I was at Finnigans from being a boy I think Finnigans 
did a bit to help me to improve. The man I got under was a very good man - he had a big family and his wife had broke down mentally and - he certainly took a big interest in me and taught me to be a good man. And - we were on piece work and he said to me,
 
he was on a rather tough job, he said, now you must be a good workman. He said, don't rush your work. Well, most of the men were more interested in getting money our of them - he wasn't. He said, if you're better than they I'll be satisfied. And I - I mig
h
t have been better in some things but I - I certainly wasn't as good all round. He could do anything. But one thing he could never do and this is a mystery, -how it's possible for an intelligent clever man not to be able to make a bow, you know, a bow - c
ouldn't do it. They used to make a ball dress weskit - a long one, and it had tapes in to pull across and fasten -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What was this for?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 To put ball dresses in - long. And they took - they had tapes in and you had to put bows on and I had to make t
he bows and when he told me he couldn't make them I laughed. He said, true. And he couldn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Who did Mr Finnigan go around with - who did that type of person go around with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Who did I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14040315\charrsid6767433 go round}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433  with? Oh Finnigan was a - isolated person I think. H
e was a - ooh he was an autocrat. They used to get out of his way when he was coming round. He used to come round the works and - look how much work they'd done and that was all and how much money they'd get and - he used to have me dogging out Mr Payen. 
He - I remember he was calling the case one time -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Mr Payne was the foreman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
He - he was dogging out for the boss so he could get rid of this case - he made a bloomer on it and - I used to go to read the paper - I used to take the bucker, the pap
er and - the - me hands were full and I used to open the door with me behind - I nearly knocked him known. So I said, I'm sorry. Rushed away and - he said I think that boy of yours is frightened of me. I was. So - he found me sat down one time. He said, m
y
 son doesn't sit down to work. His son didn't sit down at all. He didn't work so much. He's the boss living now. Anyway he - he was supposed to be in the engineering line. He said it'd be better if you stood up. And I - I stood up while he was there but t
h
at was all. We used to sit down stitching for a week. He said, are you afraid of me? I said, yes Sir. Said are you? I said, yes, I'm afraid of you. Said - what - why? I said, I don't know but I'm afraid of you. I was. I was afraid of him catching me or so
mething and - anyway this wet on until I became a man and I was sergeant in the Army and I went to camp. And I got this.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What sort of people do you think went to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14040315\charrsid6767433 church and}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433  what type of people went to chapel
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well - I - I'm not - I don't question 
different denominations. I'm a Catholic and I think I'm right but I'm not saying they're wrong. The old gentleman that used to live next door before this young couple. He had to go until the poor old fellow couldn't go any longer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 And he was chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Superintendant of Sunday school and he couldn't had his water and he had to stop and she used to get onto him - she used to nag him awful. She was all right is her own way but she was chapel mad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What was the difference between church people and chapel do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
I - I don't know. I don't know. But - she thought clergyman were something out of the ordinary - I don't - they're child - they're God's workmen like - mind I respect them and all that but I don't think they're anything - only na
tural people doing God's work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
You don't think there was any difference - you don't think the poorer people went to church or poorer people went to chapel or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No. I don't think they - grade of people go - I don't think it makes any difference
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Where you lived were all the people in the working class or lower class did they have the same standard of living did you think or do you think they had different standard
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No, I think we lived far - out of what could be got I think my mother did much better than most of 'em - in the way of feeding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 But were there different standards in Greengate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I'm sure - my father was stricter than anybody else in the neighbourhood.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Do you think in Greengate there different people who had different standards of living?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well there were - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Ashton Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 was one standard - poor. Fleet Street was - oh it was awful - much lower - it were lower than normal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 In what way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Poor. They were living - well, under a horrible condition.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Broken windows. The - it was - really you couldn't believe the difference in two streets. Mixed up with Jews and thieves and - 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Ashton Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} they weren't too bad - they were - they weren't all saints but they weren't too bad. They were very hard worked anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 This was the difference you felt in Greengate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Yes. Well, they didn't all work in Fleet Street. Chip choppers and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Some were rough and some respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh - well, they were more respectable in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Ashton Street
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 than they were in Fleet Street. There was chip choppers - there's no - no discredit to chip choppers but they lived like chip choppers - they didn't have a decent house - didn't try to have a decent house - and all that sort of thing. D
idn't have a clean house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What do you mean by chip choppers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Chopping chips and selling them in bundles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Chopping chips you mean - chopping for firewood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Yes. Yes. Firewood.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 And they were considered rough were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Yes, we
ll they - they was - there was at least one family, I think there was two did it in Fleet Street - there was nobody did it in Ashton Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Chopped chips all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well, yes, they got a living. Whole family's in it - children going round with'em and {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Ashton Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} you - the houses looked decent. The flags were washed and - oh, they were a better type of people in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
Street}}Ashton Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. Although as I say there was a criminal opposite to us. The lady that her husband was in jail and she had another pal
. Oh, she had more than one. Smart woman too. But that was the way of life I understand with these people. My mother used to warn me against her - never let her get - never - she invited me to - one day something happened she said come and sit here. I sai
d, oh no thanks. My mother says I haven't to come in. Says, all right. Oh I told her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did your mother and father have the ideas about people in different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I think my mother - me father felt all the people in Greengate were bad people I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What did your mother feel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
She thought they were - she thought - she didn't think there was any bad people I think. They were - they were as good as they come she thought.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did your mother think of herself as belonging to a certain class of people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
No. She didn't. She never - she didn't believe in - that she belonged to any class. She believed she had a duty to perform and she tried to perform it in her own way and I think she did marvels. And - but she never - she was no class dis
tinction. She didn't agree with people that were violent - the Tracey family, they were out - everybody knew them. They were downright villains.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 In what way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh every way. They were thieves. The women were had women - real bad woman. One sloped
 with a doctor. The doctor must have been had. And they were bar maids some of them 'til they got a bit older and then they went to lob.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Lob. Went to bad. Lob - - made love. Annie, the eldest daughter she was always getting locked
 up. They used to put her on a hand cart and take her on a hand cart.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Is that true?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Where to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 There was one - a family named Murphy had the first house in Fleet Street. He was a tailor - nice man Mr Murphy. Their children were no
 good. And the mother, she was - they Ir - very Irish, he was high class tailor. They hadn't a stick in the house and he used to take several policemen to lock her up and they always had to take her on a hand cart. That was Fleet Street. And Murphy that p
oor fellow, he put up with it. And both the boys - family Williams - they lived off {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Springfield Lane{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. They were a gentle family. The mother was a - ex - schoolmistress and she drank and the father he'd been a printer at Leads and they'd come from Leads. The
 boys were all on the altar - they were all good. And they taught me to be alter boy. And I used to have to go - there was nobody there before I knew the job properly to get 'em up to come and serve {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}Mass.{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} And the mother - I knew one family that she used to
 write letters to a soldier son for. And it was only for money for beer. And - he was a very nice old man and - I - I've laughed about Arthur who was a gentle fellow and - he'd been to church one Sunday morning, he's going down Greengate and there's two p
eople fighting. So he went to separate them - they stopped fighting and set about him - the two of 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Do you think it was possible with the people round Greengate could they move up in the world and come better do you think - in their jobs and that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Oh, a lot of 'em - they lived in houses that was let off - part of Greengate. Men living in old houses like - we call them does houses - lodging houses they were. Coming from church one Sunday morning - I was - I'd been with Jamie and as we're passin
g there's one criminal said, good morning Billy. And I - He was supposed not to be too bad with 'em you know, they - well, he'd been in jail. My sister turned round and - don't you speak to us, you scoundrel. So I winked at him behind her back like and - 
all right, Miss.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Do you think anyone from Greengate moved up into a better class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well I think I moved but I went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Lower Broughton{\*\xmlclose} and then a bit -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Other people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No, people never moved if they could help it. My own - I wanted them to move for years but they wouldn't have none.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Do you think they became better people - moved up in the world -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I don't know. I - I think - well, I don't know - I can't say - I wouldn't judge that. But - talking about this Red Shelly - he was a re
al criminal - he used to get five years for penal servitude. And - one night I was powerful fellow - and the eldest lad, our eldest lad, he was a beauty - the one that turned out loyal - beautiful lad. He had beautiful - curls and one used to hang on his 
h
ead - ear. Until somebody told me it was unlucky so I cut it off and I had it in a box. And - when they told me it was unlucky to keep it I burnt it. But it was a nice when I burnt it as when I cut it off. But - I'm carrying him and I said when to Greenga
t
e, we'll go through Greengate. My wife said, what for - I don't want to go through Greengate. Now, it's a long time since we went through anyway come on. So we get through Greengate and - I spotted Red Shelly before we got up to him. I said how do, I said
 how do, what are you doing out? So he said, oh, not so bad in there you know when you're used to it..
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Prison he was talking about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Yes, this is what he said. I said, you're used to it all right. They'll soon have you. Well he said, its - get - 
not so bad. So, said, oh, good bye - I'll not see you no more. I don't think I ever saw him again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 You never know a family that moved up in the world from there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh, I know plenty of families that moved.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I mean that went up in the world?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Oh, some went - yes, some - there used to be one family that were - Liberal agents - Pew. They - they moved out - they were printers too - they moved up to Higher Broughton I don't know what - they were pretty well up in the world. But they went a lot 
higher. Oh, there was some families that were quite - Walkers the toffee shop people, they did very well. Mrs Lee she died her - her husband was a scoundrel and - her son was a scoundrel - it was a pity - she was a grand person but she died when she was o
l
d. She lived in - stopped in Greengate but - she lived - finished up in a room, she did. And - oh, I knew a lot - quite a lot of people. The Bartons did better. They moved out like and - the quite a - a decent people did - decent later they moved - Greeng
ate got worse - they moved out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Do you remember anyone being referred to as a real lady or a real gentleman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 In Greengate? Well I think everybody called my - yes, I do, a remember a real lady. The woman at the pub. Mrs Dalton. Everybody called he
r a real lady and she was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
She'd help anybody, like, if she could - a down and out. She had a friend - a girl friend that became an habitual drunkard and she used to come out of Strengeways and call to see her - wouldn't give her a drink. I
t was - she'd come out - come out of jail - she'd been in - oh, I think it was over a hundred times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 She'd come to see and she'd give her some money but she wouldn't let her have a drink in her pub.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What had the girl been in prison for do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Drink every time - nothing else. She was simply a drinker - habitual drunkard. And it was a girlhood friend of hers. But Mrs Dalton was a perfect lady. My mother, Mrs Lee and Mrs Walker nursed her - when she died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Was your mother or father ever treated or referred to in this way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Oh I shouldn't think so. Couldn't call me father gentleman. I don't know as they called me mother a lady but they called - everybody called her a very good old - I dare say they did. Everybody kn
ew Mrs Finn. Yes, I think they did call her the good old lady.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Showed your mother respect did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh, everybody respected her - everybody. From the worst. And if - anybody had laid a finger on her they'd be got killed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Your home was rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Rent.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you ever see the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Saw him regular.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What did you think of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 He was a very nice chap. He was an agent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 You never saw the landlord himself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I don't know - I couldn't tell you who owned 'em. I don't know who did own them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Do you remember feeling that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet and how did you feel about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Didn't like it - didn't - I - it used to hurt me but what could I do about it - I couldn't do anything about it
 - I had to do the best I could and I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What happened if your father was ill or out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh we had to do the best we could. He'd get out of work say I suppose but it wouldn't be much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you ever have to go to anybody for help - the parish for instances?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Never. We never went - for any help of any sort. No. Never. We managed without that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Were you ever given lessons by your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Given lessons? They couldn't read or write.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Which school did you go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 St Peter's - Greengate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What type of school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh, it was a Roman Catholic school. Very -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Was it mixed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No - mixed - no, no, not in the same room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 They were in the same school but not in the same room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well it - different parts.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 How did you get to school - how long did it take?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh it only took me a few minutes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Who went with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Nobody went with me. I don't remember anybody going with - from being young - I suppose they must have done but I found me way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Where did you have your dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Dinner? At home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 You always came home for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What did you think of school - did you like it or dislike it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Horrible. I - I - it was like - I thought this much of it. Being real
ly - I never failed but being released was like a bird being - escaping from a cage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh, I liked the teachers. And - I liked one, Miss Burns, she was very nice with us. But the old schoolmaster, he was a tou
gh guy - he didn't believe in anybody being nice with you. And - he was an old villain I think. And I told you what happened.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did they teach you that certain things were right - like manners or tidiness or punctuality or ways of speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I was always punctual. I never spoke - I don't think I spoke too bad - I don't know, I couldn't tell you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did they teach you how to speak?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I think Finnigans improved me speaking I think. I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did they teach you anything about manners at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh aye. Religion and manners.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 If you did something the teachers didn't like how did they punish the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well they give - the teacher - they sent you to the schoolmaster for cane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What about the girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I couldn't tell you, I don't know much about the girls teaching.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 You don't know what they gave you the cane for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I got it for nothing sometimes I thought.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What were the other things they used to cane you for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well - Billy Duffy he was the best school - 
scholar in the school. He - he got it for me telling him - mental - answers. I was - miles in front of anybody else for from being in the fourth standard at mental and Billy he was marvelous on the book but mentally he was a dud and I used to have him nex
t to me and whisper. Then we both got it if the schoolmaster caught us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did your parents take an interest in your schoolwork - did they ever ask you what you did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh yes. Oh yes. It - they wanted me to do well and I wanted to do well for 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did they ever visit the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 My father never visited the school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Oh me mother went to see the schoolmaster if anything was wrong with me. Like for - when I got me hands marked. May - he knew me mother. Oh she must have brought me I think because - he knew her when she came I remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did she ever go to meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 She'd no - no need to go to the teachers. I - don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did the children in the school all come from the same types of home as you did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh no, there was some a bit more - more dressed up - come from Broughton. But - that's - that's who I went to Broughton with.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did the teachers treat some children differently from others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I don't know as they did. They - composition. I used to listen to it like and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Composition?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Yes. Yes. They - they read - they'd read something out to you and then you had to write it. Well when I read it myself the spelling - I used to put a query. Anyway yet when I'm writing a l
etter I query it - pretty often where the spell - I know it's wrong but I don't know how to do it right. So the best thing is to let pen know I know. I used - used to just put a mark near it. Now, I never failed. They never failed me but I used to wonder 
why I passed. I'd got the gist I suppose. I never failed in anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you have gangs or groups in your school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I was never in a gang.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you have them in school though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well I - I - I was in the - alter boy of anything - no, no, I didn't go in a gang.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Were there children ever left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Most of them wouldn't have anything to do with George. Well I wasn't like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did this happen in school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh - there was no News came to our school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Were there no children in your school left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Not that I remember. Yes, there was one family named Stevenson. There was something mentally wrong with 'em and they - they wasn't Catholics but they come - they'd sent from one school and they'd come to 
our school. One of them opened a - door and threw a glass bottle at the schoolmaster.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
For giving him the cane. And - John Willie - John Willie Heavenson he was named. They were big but there were - there were something wrong with them. He - he used to whistle like a - a bird on the fairground. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 The father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
No, this Stevenson. No, it was John Willie - he was soft. He was soft. He used to - they used to sell oil cloth and he used to run out with oil cloth like for the fello
w that shouted the prices from the top - from the stall and - John Willie was one of his butties. That's helpers like. That was a part of his job - he used to help a bit on the swings or round - about and - shows. The beer - it was a harmless thing. I wen
t in. he was supposed to be wrestling with it. Yes, he'd get a bit of anything - he didn't work but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 They were left out were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 John Willie - nobody treated him seriously and - I heard a girl shout something to him - a very rude one and - he 
said, no, you wouldn't think so. But he said some - thing very rude back - horrible. But he was - they shouldn't have plagued him - they used to plague him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you go to this same school all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh he wasn't there long - they soon carted him away from -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Were you there long?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I - I never went to any other school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 While you were at school did you ever have a part time job or did you make any money regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Never earned any money in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Wait a m
inute. I'm not sure. Wait a minute - there was a milk - an - an old Quaker's milk firm. And they used to have - boys - wouldn't say I didn't get a few copers off of that, they used to have milk carts. They had a milk shop and a pawn shop - Quakers they we
r
e - used to wear Quaker's hats and you went to the pawn shop and asked for anything and ;- they told you the price and - you mentioned a price later they didn't answer you, they shoved it back in the window. Didn't say no or anything - shoved it back. And
 I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 They had a pawn shop and a milk shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Separate shops of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 You used to help them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I - I've been in the milk carts and I - I wonder did I get any coppers for it. I don't remember. If I did it was for myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What about your first full time job - what age did you leave school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I left school - a month before I was thirteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What times did you go to school - did you go full time or part time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Full time. I went as errand boy to Finnigans in Market Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 When you were at school did you go to school for a full day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 You didn't do any half time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What time did you go to school in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Nine o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What time did you finish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Half past for - if I remem
ber rightly. Nine 'til - twelve. I think that - I - I'm not sure about this but I think this is what it was. Nine 'til twelve and two 'til half past four or five I'm not sure of that. It's a long time ago.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What about your first full time job - where was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 That was full - I didn't go in half time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 When did you start work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
I started work on - I can tell you - on - Christmas Eve - or New years Eve was it - New Year's Eve - in '94. And I was thirteen on the third of February '95. And I was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 How did you get the job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Well, my sister was dead - Lisa - and I was alter boy and the priest saw me sliding. On a slide in Greengate. So he said, William - sliding - shouldn't be doing that. It's wrong to slide at all. I said yes Father.
 So I thought oh well in the cart. I always used to feel a bit sorry for myself when I was caught. But - the next thing - a big Irish fellow with a tache up here comes to our house. The priest had sent him. He'd gone to the priest for an errand boy for Fi
nnigans. The priest had remembered me sliding so he found me a job.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 So you used to be the errand boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 So I went to be errand boy. And he used to give me - got me to do some of his work 'til me father stopped me. He was a big lazy lout.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What hours did you work at Finnigans?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Finnigans -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What time did you start in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Nine - was it - no, wait a minute - half past eight. Half past eight 'til one and two to six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you work Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Yes, Saturday morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Not Sundays, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you get holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Yes, I think - ye, yes. I think so. Yes, yes, we got holidays with pay.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Do you remember what you were paid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I got six shillings a week to start.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you think it was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh, it was a big wage for a young boy. Yes, then - they used to get about four or five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you give any of this money to your mother or did you keep it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I give it - I'd - I think I got a shilling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Do you remember what she spent the money on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh food. It was always food.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 How did you get on with the people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well - very well. But - the - manager - I - I don't think I was very posh myself - I don't think I was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14040315\charrsid6767433 very posh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433  like and - I - I - I
 know - I heard him class me with a - an engravers boy that came in that - sort of little gentleman kind of business and I used to have to sweep up and dust and go errands and - go to the engravers and - they sent me on a job with some - cutlery and I had
 
to bring it back if I didn't get the money. I were only thirteen - I thought I'm in - I'm in a right state - anyway I got - there was no difficulty - I had to get a taxi when I got to the station, it was in Cheshire. And - the taxi driver said, oh, you'll
 
get a pound. So I thought if I do you'll get none of it. Like he was - I can - I was a - I was pretty - pretty wide like - but anyway - as soon as I got there the lady - oh, she was a lovely lady, you know she sat in the hall. And she - she had a lot of m
o
ney there - she give me a pound - a sovereign, she that's for you put it away. So I put it in me pocket - I'd never had a - six shillings was the most I'd ever had - I was in me element. Anything to help me mother - it - I was happy. So - I had to get the
 
money and take it back and - oh, I was terrified of losing the money. Anyway I got in the house - told them - they were terrified of the money and I - the money's safe I said. And I pulled the pound out and I said - that's for you - to me mother. I think 
she started crying.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What did you feel about your boss - did you like him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Boss? Yes, I got to like him. And - anyway I improved - I could }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14113816\charrsid6767433 to}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433  myself I was improving. Anyway when it came to - my father said, you're not }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14040315\charrsid6767433 wasting}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433  your time there. You
'd better go to the bench. Well the system was that to go to the bench you had to be the son of somebody at the bench. The trade kept it in the - it was no good - it turned out no good anyway it's died. So - pretty well died out. Anyway - I used to go for
 
cigars for the boss - for - Finnigan and bring a - taxi for him from the taxi rank at - outside the infirmary it was then. And - he used to give me a bob sometimes. It was sometimes and all - didn't get it regular. Anyway I said, Mr Finnigan, can I speak 
t
o you? And he used to speak very sharp, yes, what do you want? Well, me father says - if I can't go to the bench I've got to leave. Says tell your father I'll make you into a good salesman. I said I don't want to be a salesman. He says I'll make you into 
a gentleman. I said I don't know about that but I don't want to be a salesman. Says no you want to go to the bench and all? I said yes Sir. My father says I've got to leave without I go to the bench. All right you can go to the bench.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 The bench was where the craft was learned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Where the craftsman worked. So -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you like your work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh, I loved it. I did - I loved it but there was no money in it for years. But - I love it yet. I - I - I have jobs yet - but anyway -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 When you got to the bench what did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did all sorts of things. I did mostly fancy work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 On leather?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 In - fancy leathers and all - crocodile, seal skin, Russian skin.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What did you make with it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Cases. Cases - yes. I made one two years ago, I'll show you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Would you have preferred any other type of occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No. I - I'd rather have me own job then anything I've ever done - think of - ever met.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 You stayed at Finnigans all your life didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No, I did twelve years at Layland Motors.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 When was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I went there in '36.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 But from leaving school 'til 1936 you were at Finnigans were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No, I'd been away from Finnigans and I left - I was away four years and a half. I did eleven months in Nortons in 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Oldham{\*\xmlclose}, a fibre firm, but - I had a - a kind of - semi }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14040315\charrsid6767433 nervous}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
 breakdown and for a period too. But I only did that eleven months at Nortons between leaving Finnigans and going to Layland Motors.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you serve an apprenticeship for your job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 For seven years.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I went on courses and I was supposed to study things - I passed 'em but I never studied 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you belong to a trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh always - I was very - I was chairman of the union. Leather union - that's defunct now - it's died out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you feel that workers and employers both had the same interests or did you think they had different interests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh - different of - there was only Finnigans that was any good, up to the standard at that period. Eventually Finnigans deteri
orated and they - they were a back number. Now Finnigans were handicapped in this way. The manager had - he was a very nice man if you didn't want any money but if you did want any money he was a very poor fellow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 So you feel he was only interested in making money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 He was only interested having a easy job and - getting away with it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What do you think the workers felt about the work - what interests did they have in the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I don't think they had any interest, the family didn't take interest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 The workers though - that worked for Finnigan?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
The workers - the workers died off and he wanted me to have the oldest lad at it. He wouldn't have been any good at anything like - at the bench. I said, no, I'm not putting nobody to it. S
aid, what anybody to this? Well there's not enough - there's not enough, I said, I can't educate my children out of it and you're asking me to put my children to it? Not likely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What do you think the difference was between what the ordinary workers felt about the work and what the boss felt about the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Well - the boss - they were sorry. The Managing Director, Archie Wood, I used to say not much for this manager at the work and for Archie Wood that was Direct - Managing Director, Deansgate. He
 was a character, Archie was. We had a dance and we went to this dance and he give us a dinner but - before that - long before that - I called when the war was over - funny thing, I took work. Most of them were interested in making money of course. You we
re there for money and the boss they'd let some of them make money and they wouldn't let some make money - they expected some to - when I say - they didn't stop 'em making money but they expected a high standard of work off some than others.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Well, because you've established it yourself. You was a good workman and you and to keep to that. Now - excuse me - that standard kept you there when they had to lay people off. But it was no used to you 'cos you was on short time and getting no money out
 hardly. I never was sacked. I'd have perhaps been better off it I had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Do you think there was a difference between trained craftsman and others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh, - of course. Anyway - when the Secretary had finished - he was a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Do you feel that there was a division of interest amongst workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
They were mostly - they were - what was popular then. Free trade and what was the other - there used to be shouting for free trade and - the other was taxing stuff coming in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 You thought there was a difference in interest in this?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
I forgot. Some were for free trade and some were against free trading. I didn't know what I was - I thought I was Labour. So I - I wouldn't - I'm not much of a politician - I think that all -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did full time work change your attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No. No, I - I've been quite satisfied to be a workman. I didn't want to be any - thing else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 When you left school did you still stay at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh, I left - was home until I got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15881451 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did going to work change your relationship with your parents at all - or your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
No. No, I was a - a - I was a - oh, I can't say I was homely but I wanted to flit from there and they wouldn't. I wouldn't leave home at any price. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh, I wanted to be with my parents. And - under any circumstances.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What about your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well me brother got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15881451 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433  and he - he moved away from home and - then there was only me sister and me - me other sister had died - Liza, so there was only me sister and me and she had a very tough time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you still }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14040315\charrsid6767433 go to Sunday school and church }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 on Sunday after you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No, I didn't - I didn't go to Sunday school before that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 You said you used to spend your spare time mostly playing football and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14040315\charrsid6767433 
playing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433  in the streets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No, not playing football. Watching football. But I played football a bit. I got into trouble for kicking the ball about the streets.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What did you do when you started work - what sort of entertainments did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well - I started work now - fourteen. I used to go to brought on play with my pals. Then I started dancing when I was about - seventeen.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Who did you go with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Some workmates - I used to go to a rather suspicious place off {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
Street}}Oldfield Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 they called it the Criterion. Used - used to go twice for sixpence. You paid sixpence to go in and got a free ticket. For a - during - now how did that work - wait a minute. I didn't go Saturdays and I didn't go; oh, I used t
o go to the Queen's Hall Saturdays. Finnigans, that was a bit later perhaps. I used to - I spent a lot of time -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Who did you go out dancing with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Pals. Now you mentioned a group. We did get into a group - dancing group. But that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Boys and girls was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No, there wasn't girls in it. No, no, no. I never was in a group where there were girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Where did you meet your friends that you went dancing with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Dancing I think. Now wait a minute - I don't know. They were from Broughton but I don't know when I met them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you have any special friends at this time - either boys or girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh the girls - I never was in any group with girls in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did your parents meet your friends - did you bring them home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Not much. Well I brought one or two but I didn't bring many - I wasn't very proud of Greengate - I didn't bring 'em home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did your parents want to know where you were going?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh yes, they wanted to know where I'd been and all about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you have to be in by a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Well I was supposed to be - but I didn't arrive. Me father used to wait up for me and get on to me. But I - I - I think I was a bit cheeky. Put up with that but - anyway I was a parent respecter but I can't say I loved me dad.
 He was too tough. Big man. And he expected more than - more than he ever did anyway but anyway there it is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
When there was trouble or someone in the district whom the people disapproved of very strongly was there any special way that they showed it. Do you ever remember anyone being made to leave by rough music and did they ever make a dummy of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Now we - I'll put it this way. We wasn't one of the community of people that got into trouble. My father wouldn't have anything to do with trouble 
at all and - we weren't allowed even to watch rows. But we - I watched 'em but he didn't know - I didn't let him know but - I can't say that I know much about what happened to the people in trouble because I wasn't there, I had to be inside. If I was in t
he district and didn't go inside I was for it when I went in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
What happened if they did something people disapproved of, what did the neighbours do about it? Say the woman you told me about who went to lob - do you remember how the neighbours showed their disapproval of her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Oh, they used to fight. Oh the - she was an outcast. You mean the Tracays - that they used to lock up. Yes. Well the - there was one son - it was said that he died of a broken heart. He was a nice fellow. But the rest of them 
- it was a big family of them and the youngest one - they used to call him Yank Tracey - he was cheeky and - he went to school about the same age as me and - I used to keep him at a distance and he knew that - if he didn't keep at a distance he'd be for i
t so I didn't have any trouble with him. But he was - he was badly behaved but I never knew him to get locked up. But Annie, she was simply and outcast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 You mean people didn't talk to her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No, nobody looked at her that was respectable at all and 
they were a wonderful looking family the girls. Beautiful looking. And Agnes, one of them, she was on the stage for a bit - a dancer I can remember that, her and a girl named Black. She wasn't on long. She was off and she was - in the drags in no time. St
e
aling off men and - they got time like and - I don't - I never knew sale to steal - she was simply a - a drunkard. And she was mixed up with a little chap. He was harmless sort of fellow but there was one thing I don't understand yet, where he got the mon
ey to get drunk. They - they managed to get drunk but they never worked. Aye - he was always a mystery that - there was only one solution - they must have stole it or something but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 You never saw anybody make a sort of image of the person who'd done wrong, an effigy or image?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Well I don't know, there was - yes, I think there was a lad out of Collier Street, that was the street next to St Peter's church, several streets up from where I lived. I think he tried to imitate Paddy Tracey. He went wrong
 early and he used to want to fight people. Well, Paddy Tracey'd fight anybody - it wasn't that he could fight but they could hurt him. He was - oh, it was awful the way I've seen him nearly murdered. I've seen him fight. And he simply kept on getting hit
 until the other person was exhausted - then he used to hit them. But - the police used to come along and if Paddy was fighting or - come on. And he - he knew he was for it. He never argued with the police much. I've seen them abuse him shocking.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 But you never saw anyone make a dummy of anyone else if they'd done something wrong?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 A dummy? No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Would you have stayed at school longer id you could have done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Not a second. I'd have liked to have left before I left.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you attend any evening classes or part time education.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I went about twice to a shorthand class and that was enough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I don't know. No. I - I don't know - I - I've managed without it. I can spell badly - me 
arithmetic a always been very good - it was positive from - I think it's a gift - it is in my grandchildren too. And me children. They're all good. But - no, I've no regrets. I - I've been a great reader - oh, me eyes, I've got cataracts now and I can't r
ead so much - my sons put a - an arrangement over the bed. I can read upstairs but I find a difficulty in reading - he's going to make some arrangement - he hasn't a lot of time - he's going to make some arrangement for me to read downstairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Do you think you benefited from your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
From my education? Oh a lot. Oh yes. Yes. I think I told you then that I served me time under - Mr Payna he was a grand chap. Plain little man but - he formed my character I think a bit. And - he always told me 
to be as good at anything as I could. Even at work. Our work was piece work and some of them that had apprentices used to want to make money out of the boys - he didn't. Never mind the money - and he had a family of children - and he had a very unfortunat
e
 happening to him, his wife went mental - she was in Prestwich for years and - anyway we - I don't know whether by example, he made me be - I wasn't bad - I never was bad - I never was inclined to be bad but I'm not blowing myself up but is true, I never 
wanted to be - anything that was wrong and I despised that were - used to live that sort of life. As a boy I did. Right from being a boy I thought you're terrible. And I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 You served your time - how long did you have to serve?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Seven years. Fourteen to twenty-one. The last year -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Tell me about the piece work - you did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Well - piece work - the firm - I think they wasn't fair. We had a manager, he was a gentleman to talk to he was a splendid speaker - a wonderful scholar and he had the rep
utation of being a wonderful musician, he used to play - the organ at a church but - my belief - he claimed to be an agnestic. He was belonging to Catholic family but he broke away from that and he was an organist at some other church. I used to take his 
love letters to a lady but he didn't marry that one he }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15881451 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
 a lady from the shop. Beautiful girl. But he told me himself as a man that she give him a dogs life. She'd no time for him. She was slim girl - oh no weight at all and I saw her - later on in li
fe and - I couldn't believe it - she was - she'd come to the works and she was - it was an awful effort to get up the stairs - she must have been twenty stone. Anyway she died and left him and he was on his own and he said he couldn't get housekeepers to 
suit him and - he was on his own. He used to have a daily help - housekeepers there was something wrong with - him or he didn't want them or they didn't want him or something. He had two nieces.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Can you tell me all about your apprenticeship and your piece work?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Well you serve seven years and the last year you worked as a man but you only got half your pay. You was paid the firm back for allowing you serve your - time kind of business. Now the man that you was under while you were serving your tim
e - your wages came out of his money. Mind you - you earned a lot more than he give you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 So he actually paid you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well he - the firm paid you but it was stopped out of his money you see. It was according to how old you was how much you got. I co
uldn't tell you now. It was started at round about six shillings even at the trade. I don't think there was any rise going to the trade. But - the work - the man you served your time under used to give you some spends as well. Now Mr payen I thought was a
 
wonderful man to me because he - he needed the money but he wouldn't let me work too hard, he wanted me to be a highly skilled man, which I became. I'm not saying it because I want to - I was. I was in the window showing - for a - representing the firm - 
workmen - in 1926.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What do you mean in the window?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Civic week - Deansgate. They had a window with a workman in - this man has worked here 1926 - I'd been there then - 19 - '82 - '94 - from 1894 New Year's Eve I went just before I was thirteen. And in 1926 I was in the window Civic Week in 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Manchester{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 for a month and then I was in the window where Foldens is now that was - Foldens is now that was Marks and Spencers. Well I worked in the window Civic Week that's right - I had a month from - Civic Wee
k In Deansgate - that was the big firm - shop. I had a fortnight in the shop opposite Lewis's - the original shop - Picadilly - that was the - new is Foldens that was before Foldens Marks and Spencers. Now I - that was six weeks altogether in the window s
howing them how to do the job. Now I did -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 The public used to watch from outside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Yes, yes. And - I was - there was expanding cases - remember those expanding cases that had a ratchet on - a fool idea but it made a million money for the people th
at patented it but it was no good it was - and it wasn't a new idea - it - the only thing that was new about the idea was the rather that was attached - the two parts of the case was the old travelers sample case that they used to take - have a man pushin
g
 round his samples and they had leather cases with top and bottom just the same as the expanding case - they had it - done - they didn't even have a firm - Australians they were. They had firms making them - for them - patented the ratchet and made a mill
i
on pound. Now this - is was a fool idea and the part I was doing in the window that man didn't do it, never mind me, I didn't do a lot of things that they did - man - woman did the stitching - today machines do - it - women don't do it. The trade is alter
ed altogether, practically died out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 But you were saying to work at Finnigans was really something in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh - if you - if you - if you was one of the head nuts it didn't say you got the most money - you was one of - the head nuts was one
 of the skilled people and if there was any sacking you didn't get the sack. But - if there was no work you got no money either did you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 How did the piece work Mr Finn?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well you used - if you was work - doing repair work you - you got ninepence 
an hour. Now if you was an piece work you could earn as much as you could earn. And if they were busy enough the firm would let some people that were after the money earn it without doing the job very well but if you was one of the people that was food wo
rkmen that they looked to for good work they expected it off you they didn't expect you to dash the work about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 So you didn't make as much money as the poorer worker?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No we didn't - didn't make as much. You made it - I was never stopped which was
 rather unusual from being an apprentice until the firm closed I was never stopped.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Why - did they stop a lot of people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well - seasonal they used to be flat. Trade used to be go down and they used to stop work and - if they got enough stopped 
they didn't want man they sacked them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Could they get a skilled leather worker easily?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
They - they - I made leather - work as well. Heavy leather work. Called them state rooms. They were cabin trunks - very heavy leather with steel bands in the 
body and hoop iron in the top and - ooh, an elaborate thing - terribly heavy. Gentleman suitcase - fool idies. It - it lasted forever and they used to have wood in the end and - that was to make it strong but it was too heavy before they put anything in i
t and they did away with all that eventually. The trade's altered and the fibre - thin that comes along that we have nothing to do with - the lighter case has a soft top and bottom - some Birmingham firm make that - they're not }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740007\charrsid6767433 portmanteau}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433  marks - they're n
ot leather workers even. So the trade excepting - there's a Jewish firm that still does crocodile work in London and they pay practically any price if they can get a man equal of the job of doing it but they can't get a man because nobody's serve their ti
m
e to it eventually - it was no good. And if they did serve their time to it there was nobody to show 'em how to do it properly. But Walskies - I think it's Walskies - in London still make crocodile work but it's - that's London and - I think they're the o
nly firm that do it now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 You did tell me that you were an official in a union - can you tell me about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well I was - first of all I was Assistant Secretary all you did them - Mr Payne was the Secretary, I was his assistant.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Was it just a leather workers union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 It was only the portmanteau makers union. It was a - it was nothing. A little branch. Eventually we joined with 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose} and - the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Manchester{\*\xmlclose} branch is died out all together but the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} branch is still going. There's a bit of
 work in London. But - they send me a pound every Christmas - now. Yes. But I send six shillings benevolent money and they send me a pound is it's a good deal. But - the leather trade also gives me - now this is not the trade - this is the leather trade f
o
r the country - the leather trade gives me fifteen shillings a week. Now you've got to be recommended by your trade as being a good person and - did everything beneficial to the business and helped - our chief organizer that was an apprentice younger than
 
me came here and told me about this. Oh I said, I don't need this. That - when I was - just after I'd left work. And - he said your having it. There's people in - my wife was ill and he said - people in much better position than you that's done less than 
you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did they have anything like this in the olden days before 1918, this little union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
I didn't know about - oh the little union used to have a draw at Finnigans. Just a - - it was only - Finnigans was the - really was the union for this part.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What did this union actually do though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well, you were supposed to - you wasn't supposed to work at home. You - you were supposed to do a lot of things that you didn't do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Such as what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well they used to go in - this is the type of old
 man that was at the trade when I first went. They used to wait with tall hat and frock coats and they hadn't tuppence. They used - it's a fact - they used to borrow money to go and have a drink in the pub.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 There were union officials?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No, these were the workman. Oh the union officials were just }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14113816\charrsid6767433 a bit}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
 higher graded. But - well they picked them out - it was their vote. They used to come drunk to the meeting. They hadn't been home - they'd been having a jar or two and I said to them, I - I'll go and
 see this business so I went and listened to them yarning and - in the pub and - their wives had got no money sometime. They used to be on the beer and booze the money and - she got none. Anyway - I said - they made me President - Chairman - it was nothin
g
. Little union, it was only a small thing altogether. And - they - I think some of them come drunk and I think I was a bit hard faced myself. Said if some of you fellows could make portmanteaux as good as you can talk in the; pub you'd be all right - but 
you can't. Oh. Uproar. It's true. Anyway - they - they died - off but - it's a fact they used to come a tall hat, frock coats and they hadn't a penny. And they used to be -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did this union serve any purpose - do you think it did any good?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well, I
 - I think it did. It - it was a sweaty job and some sweaters were inclined to do work at home if they were allowed. Well it covered that a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What do you mean sweated work - they'd take work home to pad out the piece work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well, if you didn't
 watch - they've been caught taking work out. From work to do it at home - but - they'd do foreign as they called it, outside, which wasn't allowed and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What difference did this make if they did work at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well, they're letting - they're - trade claimed that they were damaging the trade by being competitive without }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740007\charrsid6767433 expense}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
 kind of business. They were unfair traders. And they were getting advantage over the parson that only worked at the bench. Whether it's right or not I don't know - I'm not 
questioning it. But - that - that was the rules of the old people. And than when it was suggested that we'd amalgamate with {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 I was on the committee and oh, I was all for this. And old Mr Payne said, you're making a mistake. I said, am I? So he said, 
we'll be non-existent in no time. I said, we're non-existent now for the use of us. Said, we're no use. All right, have it your own way. Anyway - they pensioned Mr Payne off at a pound a week and I was very glad. And when they suggested it to him I said, 
t
ake it. 'Cos this firm's collapsing. Said, I don't want you to leave for my benefit - for your benefit, you take it because in a bit they'll not be giving it. And it did collapse I don't know what happened if there was anybody still on pension but he died
.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What actually happened during this seven years of your apprenticeship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 You served your time and you - you - you - the - used to be all hand stitching. It was ridiculous the amount of stitching that was put in.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 On the whole of the case?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Everything was hand stitched. And the boys used to have to sit down and - sit down at a bench and stitch for a week. Oh, I can stitch real - I think I can stitch with me eyes shut yet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 You did this the whole of your apprenticeship did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 We
ll - you gradually did more. You gradually learnt to do other things besides stitching. Stiffening. That's making them with glue or paste. Solid leather - heavy leather - work used to be - made stiff - it used to be wet, rolled out - sleeked out they call
ed it on the back - made flat and then - then very heavy paste - paper pasted on and put up to dry and it dried hard. They made them to les forever. I bet they're lasting yet some of 'em that was made then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you say you started there at six shillings a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I did - I started as errand boy at six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you stay on that the whole time you were apprenticed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No, no. As an apprenti}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740007\charrsid6767433 ce}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433  you want up a shilling a year. A shilling a year if I remember rightly. I think I remember rightly. I think I was getting about thirteen and six when I was twenty. And some spends.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Who decided whether you got this rise - the man who paid you out of his own earnings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 The man's money - you used to get it from the firm but it was taken out of his earn
ings. Taken out of his earnings and he used to give you spends as well. Perhaps half a crown - three shillings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What - would his earnings be like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh, he'd be earning between two and three pound a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Which was a lot of money in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Oh it was - lot of money. Well I was supposed to earn about two pound a week when I come out of me time but I didn't always earn it - crocodile leather was a very - funny proposition. It used to have scars and cracks and you used to have to dodge 
it up. Well - this manager of ours -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 How do you mean dodge it up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Crocodile skin it - it grafts. If you - a scale of a crocodile - it might have a crack there. Well if you could find another scale and was able to shave it to nothing and put it o
n there just rough that a bit, put it on, it'd go to it - graft to it. Now in the vein there were often faults. You - used to have to put - put a patch in the vein and - it was really skilful work but he didn't want to pay a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740007\charrsid6767433 skilful}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433  man - and he didn't if 
he could help it. So instead of being beneficial to you it was really an handicap. You were one of the nuts like and everybody like being dressed up but kind of one of the heads kind of business and I liked me trade and I liked to be clever at it but I di
d
n't get paid for it and - as I tell you I was the window man Civic Week and they had a bench set up in the firm - in the shop for people to go and have a look. They were working on the bench in the shop. I was in the window that the people outside saw me.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you like your boss there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
I think I did. Ooh, but he was a martinet. Oh dear. Billy Finnigan. He - he was a wonderful business man but he died before the change went over.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 How did you get on with the people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 All ri
ght. I - I've only - in me life - there's only one man I couldn't get on with and at the finish I didn't try. And I came across him in the fibre world. Now it might have been unfortunate but he's an apprentice in the first world war and - he was taken pri
soner - in his apprenticeship.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 When you were at Leyland Motors what did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well, it's surprising, on the old buses, how much very simple leather work it was there - straps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What year were you there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I went to - in the year '36 and left in '48 - twelve years. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What was your time of starting at Leyland Motors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 We used to start at quarter past eight. I used to get the six o'clock train from here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Was it a good wage there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Money for nothing. Compared with Fin
nigan it was like - you couldn't compare it better than saying they shoveled it to you. You got as much money - that was the foundation - you was on engineers money and then they used to pay you bonus. And the bonus was terrific. Oh, I could never underst
and it. Perhaps at Finnigans on short time I'd be getting about fifty bob and now I were getting eight pound and more Well it was marvelous. And they used to give you double pay twice a year. Ooh, it was - it - well, it was money for nothing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 You were doing leather work there too were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Well - simple things - little straps. Now on a bus - they used to make all sorts of gadgets to cover the gear box, to cover the brake to stop the dust and - they used to have hangers, they don't have them now, 
they're out of date. Strap hangers. Check straps - they'll have the check straps yet, for the bus door - they were a pretty tough job, hard job but - you got well paid for it but - there was more work on them, they've cut it out a lot. When I went there i
n
 '36 there was quite a bit. It's surprising - I don't know where they put a lot of it but the - gaiters they used to call one thing - they used to go somewhere underneath. Anyway I was played off there once for a bit, they told me they'd send for me and -
 going home the - one - another fellow that was played off - oh he said, he tells everybody that. I said, all right, if he don't send for me I won't go. But he did send for me. Now it acted rather funny at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Leyland
{\*\xmlclose}. The - the - there was no official assis - for}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740007\charrsid6767433 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
man but there was an assistant foreman - he was unofficial but he was assistant foreman. And he used to act. And he said to me, you're a bit of an old fashioned fellow. I said, aye, and you're not. He wasn't - he was younger than me. I said, you're not
 so young either.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 You had another job in between?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Nortons - Fibre, Oldham.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What did you do there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 It was leather work. This - I'm trying to think of this fashion in - the new leather that they made - white leather it was. Made a lot o
f trunks with it. We made things - we made all sorts of leatherwork. I made leather work there. But it was - our trade was badly organized and they couldn't command a fair wage but - at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Leyland{\*\xmlclose}
, tell you they }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740007\charrsid6767433 shoveled}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433  money at you. They did really. And - i
t - I was coming to tell you that the part - Leyland used to be on war work and of course if they'd only enough for so many man they used to transfer you from the - the upholstery department we were in - transfer you to that to the engineers department. W
e
ll I was never transferred but I was lucky - another chap and me had to toss up and I won. But - there was - clearing out a lot of men and - oh, some of them had been there twenty years - well I felt awful. I'd only been there a bit you know and it seemed
 awful to see those chaps walking out. So I said to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What age were you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15881451 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 ?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I was twenty-five, we were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15881451 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433  on the sixteenth of November 1907 and I was twenty-six on the February next.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 How long had you known your wife?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Three years - over three years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 How did you meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Well - I told you I used to dance. Well a lady adopted me kind of business I - when I went to learn to dance but - she wasn't my type. She invited me to her twenty-first birthday and that was the end of 
her as far as I was concerned. But we went to a ball. At {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Downing Street{\*\xmlclose}
, Public Hall and - my wife worked with this - lady at Mackintoshes Rubber Works. And - I took a fancy to my wife - she couldn't dance. I used to tell her she had club feet. But - I met
 her at this dance but from seeing her I decided that it was my - in future wife. Well, I thought so. But before that I was going to London to City play in the Cup Final - 1904. And - I - I met her in town. I said, would you like to go out with me. She sa
i
d, I don't know. I said, oh, I thought you might - might, I said, well I - I'm asking you I said but I'm not asking you to start until I've been to the Cup Final when City plays for the Cup - Crystal Palace - I'm going. It hadn't to stop me going to the f
i
nal. Well - that was arranged. It was all right. Oh, she'd give it a trial. So we met outside All Saints church Sunday night. This is the night after the Cup Final and I'd had one or two. And - I was glad it started really and I thought I can get out of t
his for tonight. No. I wasn't very keen on it because I didn't want to leave me par - well there was a group of us that used to go dancing - I - I didn't - I wanted it both roads - I wanted to be courting and I didn't want to be courting. But I -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Where did she come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 She came from Books - wait a minute - Preston Street, Hume. I suppose it is, yes, Hume. And it -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you save money before getting }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15881451 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh, I saved a bit. Saved a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did your parents help you in setting up a home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No, they couldn't help me, they couldn't help themselves - I had to help them,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 How long were you engaged?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 About twelve month I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Can you tell me about your wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What did you have for presents and did you have guests and did you go on a honeymoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I forgot - we got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15881451 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
 at St Peter's - Greengate and I was born, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15881451 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433  and christened, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15881451 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433  went to school there. And - presents, I couldn't tell you off hand. We got quite a few presents. Pictures
, fire irons, brass - stand, copper kettle - oh, there was quite a number of presents. But I couldn't - I don't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you have guests - a lot of friends there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh we - the - wedding was kept up at the Marlbrough, corner of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
Street}}Preston Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, there was a lot of guests there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did your wife wear white?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I couldn't - I couldn't tell you - I don't think so. I couldn't tell you - I don't think she -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Was it a big affair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Pretty good - yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you have a honeymoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No, I don't think so. We were on short - no, we went - we went on short time just after. No, didn't have a honeymoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Where did you live after you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15881451 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Lower Broughton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Do you remember the address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I do. Number fourteen Norah Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 How many years did you live there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well we only lived there - let me see - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15881451 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433  - well we lived there about one year. I'll tell you how that came about. It - we had my first child was born nine months and a day and my wife broke do
wn with a nervous breakdown and we had to go and live with her sister for twelve months at Gorton. So we were only in Broughton in Norah Street for twelve months. Now -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Where did you go then after you lived with the sister?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Gorton. Yes. Railway Street, Gorton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 How long were you there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Twelve months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Then where did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Come back to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Colberg Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
, Lower Broughton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 How long were you - there - do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh, wait a minute, quite a bit. We came up here in '
36 and - 1907 - 1908 - 1909 - about twenty-five years I think down there. Yes. Yes. And then we came here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 How old was your wife when you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15881451 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 She was eighteen months younger than me. She was twenty-four. Her birthday was on the sixth of August.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did your wife work when she got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15881451 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well - we got very hard up and she went out to work but they'd no work so that was no use.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What did she do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 She was a garment maker at Mackinsoshes - Rubber Works.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you mind her working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I didn't like her working. I never believed in - if we could avoid it. She didn't work a lot - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Just that time at the works was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well I - I - I don't remember her working much more. I don't think she did - the children came - no, she didn't work much more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 She didn't work after the children came?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 How did she like her work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I don't know. I don't - she - well, I don't know whether she liked it or not but I didn't like it - I - I wouldn't talk about it if
 I could help it - I didn't like the idea of her working at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 How did you budget?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
I - I can tell you. Yes. Well I can tell you I gave me wife - I know what I gave her - thirty-one shillings I think it was. I gave - my mother and father eighte
en pence and I gave her father and mother eighteen - her father, her mother was dead, eighteen pence. Well - I thought it was only fair.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 How many rooms were there at the house at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Colberg Street
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Only two up and two down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 There wouldn't be a parlour - just the living room and kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No, living - vestibule, living room and the back scullery.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Were there any relatives or lodgers living with you there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No, we were - never had lodgers. Oh, me sister stayed with us very short time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did your wife have any paid help in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did she do the washing at home or send it out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 She did the washing and - when we had any children there was a lady - used to have a doctor - Doctor Beasley - and a lady used too
k after her while she had the baby.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did your wife make the clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Were they new or secondhand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No, new. They were never secondhand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Where were they bought - do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 She used to buy the stuff and make them fo
r the children - I don't know. I went and bought me own. She made - she made - oh, she made them any time. She was very clever. Run a little suit up - a frock for the child.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 This was her trade wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No, she was a garment maker isn't machinist. No, no. She - rubber. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 It's all sticking them together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Yes, sticking stuff. That was her job. Anyway she was very clever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What about the shoes - did you ever repair the shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I repaired them all. Every Tuesday night the chil
dren - and the eldest lad, he used to kick the toe - he was left handed, left footed and he used to kick everything with his left foot and he used to kick the toe off. I could put a new toe cap on in no time. Just - wedge the toe cap in a - saw off - put 
a toe cap on. No time. Oh, I was pretty useful at that. And - I repaired all the shoes until I went to the war. And - I've done a lot of it since too. I've done it until recently - I used to do it for the old man next door too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Do you remember where your childrens shoes were bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No. I couldn't tell you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 When did they have shoes - do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh, they had them when they wanted them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you help your wife with the housework - with the cleaning or cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No. I tell y
ou what - that reminds me, I used to shell peas. And - she'd - she'd say there'll be none left. By the time you've finished with that job. No, I didn't do much housework.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you ever wash up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 When she was in bed - I think she had to be in bed for me to wash up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What about laying the fires - who did the fires?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
No, I - I hate fires - I hated them and I hate them now. Have to light them now but if there's any getting out of lighting a fire I gave - get out of it yet. And if there's any sign of the weather being decent there's no fire.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What about decorating and repairs and improvements to the house - did you do those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I - this - this is going to be funny too. Now - my - work really was - some of it was pasting and I wasn't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14113816\charrsid6767433 b}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 ad 
but I didn't like housework. Now my wife did - she liked paper hanging, she liked painting. So - when she was doing some paper hanging she used to put it on and I used to - help her a bit but I was so much help that she'd say go out and have a drink. Out 
o
f the way. True. Now the - this passage here - she stated to do the paper hanging there and her eyes - she had cataracts - and when - the first - lot up, I said, wait a bit, I'll do that. I could see it - she couldn't do it. So of course when I started to
 
do it I did the job properly - right up to the top of the stairs. When she saw it she said it's beautiful - she put her hands round me neck and kissed me. I said, aye, but it's not regular. So when Mr Pickering - the old gentleman from next door - come in
, oh, she said, Mr Finn's done the lobby and the landing and the staircase beautiful - have a look. So -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you help with the children - undress them or bath them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No, I didn't undress them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you tell them stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No, I didn't bath them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you tell them stories or read aloud to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
No, I didn't. Their mother used to - she did all that sort of thing. I used to take 'em out when they were - children that you could take out. Take 'em to see my friend - that was blowing off for me. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you look after the children when the mother was out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Oh, if she was out I certainly looked after them. Oh they were - I never neglected the children if I was about. But I wasn't about so much - I used to be out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did the children have jobs to do in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Not much. I think their mother did most of the jobs - no. She was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What time did they go to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh, they went to bed fairly early.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did they put themselves to bed or did one of you put them to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No, mother took them to bed and read stories to them and - and - oh, she was a wonderful lady.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did the children share a bed or a bedroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 They had a cot - the boys had - they had a cot when they was young and then they had a bed and - the girl had a bed for herself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you have enough bedrooms for them each to have a bedroom at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
No, the bedroom - here - they didn't have a bedroom to themselves. They'd - the girl's bed - there was a division cloth between - the lads bed was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 The other side of the cloth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 That's right. Anyway - eventually that was altered. We - the box room - the boys went in the box room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Where did they bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Bathe? Oh, we had a big tin bath.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 How often - when?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh every week regular - everybody had a bath Friday night. I used to go to the baths.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 You went to the public baths?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Yes. I went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 When did they have clean clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh, all complete changing every week. And that - that continues yet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Where did you eat your meals at - colberg Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 In the - the front room was the - the living room - the vestibule and then you were in the front room - it was a nice little house. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 But you only had that one living room there didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Living room and a back scullery - big back scullery.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 You'd no room you could go for special occasions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Where did your wife cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 In the back scullery.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did she have gas or did she have a range?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 She had - she had something of
 the sort that - it wasn't a range, it was a stove. Yes. She used to cook on the fire too in pans. She was wonderful with soups and broths - wonderful. Was really. I - I'm very fond of pea soup - I've had it this week but it's not me that's cooking it, it
'
s her - yet. I couldn't cook cold water until I had too. When she was ill mind you - she was bedfast over three years so I had to learn to cook and I had to go very careful because - like, she used to tell me what to do and I - I eventually - well, it's b
een useful to me since. I cook the dinner for meself now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 When was breakfast eaten when you were all together as a family when the children were with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well - I went to work - earlier than them I think, before they had their breakfast I think so. I - I certainly did to 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Leyland{\*\xmlclose}. I used to catch the six o'clock train and I not - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Oldham{\*\xmlclose}
 I went earlier and I think I - I had me breakfast when I went to Finnigans before them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Who gave you breakfast - your wife?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh yes. She - gave all the breakfast. Yes. I didn't let her give me me breakfast at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Leyland
{\*\xmlclose}. I wouldn't let her even get up and I wouldn't let her cook it. I used to get up so I could cook it - I used to get up, cook me breakfast and shave every morning before I went and I used to catch the six o'clock train. So I was up early.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What about - the rest of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well, she used to get up and - cook the breakfast until she wasn't able to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 And all the children had it together did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well there was only two chil
dren at home - the one that - they wouldn't agree to he wasn't here. He didn't live at - home. The other two - he used to be better and he came after they went - we had to get rid of him. He - his mother was ill and he dragged himself here but the young o
ne came and insisted on him going. I couldn't look after him and my wife and myself and the house. It was impossible.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What did you have for breakfast - do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well I - I can't tell you because I couldn't eat egg and bacon before the war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 You remember at home it used to be cracked eggs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 At home. Oh, I couldn't tell you. No, I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What about dinners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh, me mother always made a good dinner of some sort.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I mean your wife?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I used to - my wife - she m
ade a good dinner of some sort. But - when I worked away like we used to have dinner at night. My wife was a splendid cook except for pastry. Sole your boots with the pastry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you have anything special on Sundays for dinner or tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 She used t
o make a cake and nobody's ever been able to make a cake to suit me like her cake. Now it - it's nothing about her cake, there was hardly anything in it - and it was dry. Now, my daughter's cake, she makes seed cake - wonderful cook, my daughter - say - t
h
e old fellow blowing off again but it's true - clever woman my daughter - she is clever. But - and so is the lad, but - she makes wonderful seed cakes - when my son had a week with her a month or two ago he brought me seed - a big seed cake and seed life 
- that. Now I'm going in a week or two and I'll bring a seed loaf back or a big cake sure. She - when she - if she does call here she has a bedroom upstairs fixed for herself but she stays at my sons - I don't worry about that - but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Do you remember what you had for teas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
We used to have greens, tomatoes, tripe. I never liked kippers, I liked herring, pickled herrings. That was one of the things I liked. Haddock, pickled herrings, liver - oh, some kind of tasty food.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Anything special for Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Sunday - used to have cakes and blancmange and, that's not much in my line, but they had cakes, blancmange and - fancies and - and I'm not much on that line but they had them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did she make her won bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 My wife - no, I've never been 
partial to home made bread - my mother used to make it but I can't say - I wouldn't be telling the truth if I didn't say I've always liked shop bread better. I liked me mother's ban cakes but - I've always liked shop bread better than home made.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did your wife make her own jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
She used to open jam - she used to make her own jam sometimes and she used to bottle tomatoes. I used to bring her a lot of tomatoes from - Leyland. I used to get some wonderful tomatoes and - they - the shelves have been f
ull of tomatoes and pickles and jam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 She made her - own pickles too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Occasionally. Not always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What about beer or medicines or wine?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Not any of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did she bottle any vegetables apart from tomatoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 She didn't bottle anything else. She - we always had a lot of vegetables - I still have plenty - quite a lot of vegetables.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you grow your own fruit or vegetables at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Never had anywhere to grow them. This is the most ground I ever had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you have tinned or dried vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh no tinned - I - I'm prejudiced against tine - no tins where it could be avoided. Of any sort.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 You've never kept hens, pigs or goats if you've not had ground?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Never kept anything like that - no. Never had any room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 How many times a week did you eat meat when your children were growing up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 How many times did I?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 The family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well the family not as often as me. I was a bit of a glutton I think. When the children were
 young I wouldn't let my wife get up Sunday morning. I used to get up cooks the breakfast, take it to bed to her and - she wasn't - she never was very strong - good health although she lived to be seventy-two, but - I used to cook myself - used to - she u
sed to get a log of mutton or pork or something and I used to cut a chunk off - a couple of eggs - perhaps a bit of bacon and a lot of bread and butter. And that was for breakfast for me. And - a dinner plate }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14113816\charrsid6767433 cram}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 med. I was a glutton I'm sure. But it hasn't killed me - you see. I - I'm still pretty useful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you ever eat tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No, I'm prejudiced against tinned meat. The - there's some comes in my parcel but that's as far as I get - I never buy any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you ever get any meat from poaching - such as rabbit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Rabbit? No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did your wife ever have to go short so that you and the children could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No. No, no, that - that - if there was any food at all everybody had it - we was never short. We managed to get along all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you have larger helpings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Ah but - there was - they were all right. I wouldn't have had it if they'd have been short. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Were your children allowed to talk during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No, I - I didn't - I wasn't strict person like - 
if they wanted a word that was reasonable - all right - but I wouldn't let them carry on a conversation.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Could they choose what they wanted to eat or did they have to eat what was put in front of them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No. If - if possible they could choose what they wanted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What did you feel like if the left something on the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh, if they didn't want it they had no need to eat it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 If they wanted something on the table like the salt did they have to ask for it or wait until it was offered?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Salt was always there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 They could ask for it if they couldn't reach?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Yes. Sure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Could they ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did they have to hold their knife and fork in a certain way or sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh they had to have a knife and fork pretty early.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did they have to hold it - in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh no. As long as it was reasonable. I don't think the old fellow held it in any special way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did they have to sit in a certain way at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did they have their own places?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Who served the meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh my wife.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Where did the younger children sit until they were old enough to come to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Children? Well - I - we used to - we had a tall chair. When they were young they used to be in that first.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Who fed them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Their mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 How old were they w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4000625\charrsid6767433 h}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 en they started to come to the table do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh perhaps two or three. Three I suppose. I couldn't tell you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 When your children were young did you feel there was a right and a wrong way of bringing up children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well - I - can tell you now, I never struck one of my children in my life. So I wasn't too strict.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you think there was a right and wrong way to bring children up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh, of course. It had to be the right way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Which was the right way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Everything was - had to be what was right. And - I'm glad to say that I didn't have much trouble only with the boy that got mixed up with betting. The others wanted t
o do things right. They were anxious to be progressive and do well. And they've done well and they were always trying to do well. And - well it made things easier. They were ambitious and they were clever and they were confident and they've - carried out 
their confidence. They weren't boastful but they were pretty sure of themselves.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you and your wife both have the same ideas about how to bring up your children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you talk about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No, we just let it occur and we agreed all right - we never }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740007\charrsid6767433 disagree}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433  on that point.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Was there anyone you used to talk to if you were worried about the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I was never worried about them. Only our George. Used to talk to me sister about him and - well you could do nothing about it
. I had a word or two with the old gentleman - he was a Sunday school superintendent but not out of sympathy - he's caused me trouble when my wife was ill like and - he was irresponsible. He wasn't wicked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 This is your oldest boy you're talking about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Yes. He was - he wouldn't stick to a regular job - he wanted to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Do you thin - that round Colberg Street some people - some families in certains groups felt that they were more better off or superior to other people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I don't think so. No. Colberg - this man - didn't live in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}
}Colberg Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, he used to live in one of the smaller streets a bit away. I don't know his name - but I knew his reputation and I knew that the woman were a bit afraid of him so -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 But there were no people thought they were superior to other people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I don't think so. There was - town inspectors, railway workers, engineers - I was a leather worker and I was working at 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Leyland{\*\xmlclose} part of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Colberg Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} but mostly at Finnigans. But the children were growing up so - 
it helped some you know. But - it was a tough business. Well - while they were young and Finnigans - very bad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Do you remember a distinction between }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740007\charrsid6767433 craftsmen}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433  and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 The distinction? Oh there was quite a definite distinction.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Well a - a - a - a lab - a man - I'm not saying that the labourer wasn't all right but a labourer's wages was round about eighteen shilling - the craftsman averaged say from thirty-six to two pound which was a - well nearly double wasn't it. D
ouble in some cases. So the standard, of course, was better. But I'm not saying they were any better.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you have a struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did I - yes, at times we'd a big struggle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What did you feel about this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well I - I wasn'
t very happy about it. It - it was frustrating - there was noon in this part of the world where I could go and - well - I could do nothing about it and I - I was miserable. Had a bit of a break - nervous breakdown at that time over it. But I got over it a
nd I - I made up me mind that nothing would ever make me break down again - well, I've never had any reason to break down again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What happened when you were ill - did you have to go to anyone for help?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well - yes, I was in hospital for a bit - short time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 But you didn't have to go anywhere for financial help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No, my son was old enough to help then and daughter. No we didn't go for any financial help at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 You didn't have to go to the Guardians?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Never. We never went for financial help.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Was your dad often ill or out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740007\charrsid6767433 Me dad}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
. He was out of work several times for rather long periods. And - one was thirteen months engineers strike. Colonel Dwyer I think his name was, he had the engineers out - they wanted more money and he had them out thirteen months I think it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 How did you live?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well, there was - unemployment pay and - my sister was working - me sister was working and - we lived very bad. Very tough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 How do you mean tough? Very short of food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Well, it wasn't elaborate food. As I told you I had to go to - for cracked eggs. Bloaters, bits - pieces of meat. Go to smithy door for giblets. That was off Victoria Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What was this smithy door?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 It - the Shambles - you know wher
e the Shambles is - well, there used to be streets of poultry dealers there and he used to be able to get a parcel of - fish, parcel of giblets for about sixpence. I didn't often go for fish but I used to go for giblets. Used to go Allens for bacon - that
 was the - the posh shop. All these things had to be done but I did it. And we had to do it. And me mother was a marvel. She fed us somehow. Got a chicken for a shilling I told you. Chicken Ann I think they call her - Mrs Maddock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Was your father often ill or out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Oh no, he worked - he hadn't - two or three rather long periods but he worked most of his life. He wasn't - a regular unemployed man. He was a hard working man but a - if he decided that the job wasn't suiting him well he - he de
cided he'd get - get rid of it and the only way he got rid of it was by - stopping off. They said he was a very good worker - he was a tremendous man. He had a thinnish face - my daughter's something like him. But I can remember him - he had a tremendous 
c
hest and arms - awful. Ooh dear. I used to frighten you to look at 'em. Anyway - of course he deteriorated. He - he stopped working when he was sixty. Lost his eye - he got nothing for that, now he would have got compensation. Lost the eye through having 
chippings in it. Didn't get a penny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 He was an an iron foundry - were they iron chippings that - he got in his eye?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Iron foundry - he was a fetler.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Were they iron chippings he got in his eye?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Yes. Yes. But the - the decent people in Gr
eengate was safe from the roughs. Safe from the criminals. It was only people that came along outside criminals and this one that spoke to me - he wasn't a local. Now, I'll tell - there's one thing about - well go into that. I told you my mother was a fri
e
nd of the lady of the district - Mrs Dalton at the - she was ill for some time and I heard a Mrs Lee and Mrs Walker used to nurse her. Well I used to come home early and go and stand on the corner of Gravel Lane and I could see my mother come out - of the
 
Bull's Head and see her - I was watching for her safety come home. So that no - lacal'd interfere with her but a stranger might. Well a chap comes out of the pub and he he offered me an handkerchief. I didn't know him. So I knew he was a stranger. Somethi
n
g like this - give me five bob for this. And he started edging towards me, well, the only way for me to stop him was to hit him or something - I'd no intention of giving him five shillings. And a woman came along - I'd never spoken to her in my life but s
h
e was known - she was known as a few things. It was doubt full whether she was a - in touch with the police to give criminals away. The man that she lived with was a big handsome man. She had a - a shop down some cellars - a big place - the thieves used t
o deal with her.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 How would they deal with her - they would bring things and she would be a sort of receiver?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I think. Well she had - whether she was or not I don't know but they said she was. She had a daughter that was a thief - used to go up t
own like and rob people and her husband they called a megs man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What is a megs man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Well the - still exist - megs men. They're confidence man - in town they'd got strangers and confidence tricksters and rob them somehow. Anyway - this woman - oo
h, she was a well known character - I was afraid of her, like she had such a reputation and - this chap had only just spoke to me - didn't know she know me. I used to pass her shop - her cellar shop going to work, on the other side. And - she said what's 
t
o do? So I said, he wants five shillings for this. And one - another criminal - schoolboy - same time as me, come out of the pub. He'd had penal servitude - Toddy Barnes. And she said to Teddy Brown - give him a good hiding. He's trying to get five shilli
ngs off Billy Finn. Well I was astonished that she knew my name but everybody know my mother, like she was such a good person that - anyway she knew me and I didn't know. So I said I thank you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Was there a lot of poverty in Greengate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well - the 
poverty in Green gate - a lot of it - they were drunkards that wouldn't work. They were - became criminals that couldn't - work - couldn't get work. Their wives drank - it was awful that. The children used to beg at - works door for bread. Frankenburgs, R
ubber works - see children bare footed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Went begging for bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Begging for bread at the door. This - well - and you'd see children stood in the pub doorways, their mothers inside. Where they got their money was always a mystery to me. They just 
have stole it somehow. I - don't know. And they'd - some of these chaps would ask you for money as you was passing. Never got it off me. And when they asked me I'd say, No, I'll give you nothing. - And - I was safe enough like there was enough I knew'd lo
ok after me to protect me but this Teddy Brown he wiped the floor with these fallow. And she said to him - if you're in - Greengate tomorrow morning you'll know about it. Get out tonight. And I heard he had to get out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 She was the master of the criminals you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Well, she must have been. She ordered this Teddy Brown to fight him and hit him. Give him - he did do. I never spoken to her - she'd never spoke to me before and she never spoke to me again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Were there any organized charities round Greengate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 They weren't organized. Weren't organized - these meg}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740007\charrsid6767433  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 men they used to come from outside. They were thieves and she - they - credited her with being an informer and a receiver. They said so. But whatever she was she was the master of crimin
als. I was satisfied of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 You said there was such a lot of poverty in Greengate - did you have soup kitchens or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Yes, we had soup kitchens at times.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Suppose a child was very hungry was there anywhere it could go to get something to eat or drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Not as a regular thing I don't think. They used to have people coming round giving them - relief.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What type of people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well relieving officer and they used to - they used to have people dogging out for 'em whe
n they were coming so they could get dressed up a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 How do you mean dressed up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well, washed and clean and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Would this make a difference to whether they got relief?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well, I suppose it did. Some of 'em used to drink. If they knew h
e was coming they didn't drink. And the - the children were dogging out for him coming. Relieving officers. Never came to our house. I never had that. We never needed that - we never was that bad. I think me father wouldn't have had it if we'd }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15740007\charrsid6767433 starved}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433  - don't think so. Oh, he was proud man. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I remembered Greengate being talked of in the police when I was in during the war and by then it had quietened down a lot hadn't it?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh, it - it - there's nothing of Greengate that used to be. I used to live in -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 How did you feel about it - were you frightened of Greengate as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
I wasn't frightened. No, I felt quite safe. But as I told you, very early I was alter boy and - used to to to Broughton to play. My friends - oh, I couldn't find f
riends in Green - only John Whittle - they kept a beer house. And I hit Johnny one time. We - Sunday school and he pulled me tie out. This - like this and it wasn't far - I said if you do that again I'll hit - you. He did it again and I knocked him down. 
A
nd - he became a councilor after - we were great friends too. Well his father was a councilor - ooh, Dick Whittle. Always had a beer house and they had a print works as well. He was about the biggest nut in Greengate - Dick Whittle. Oh no, there was Alder
man Balderstone. I don't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 He was a bigger nut was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Aye. He was - Dick Whittle was a councilor - Alderman Balderstone as a - Alderman. But - anyway - they had grocer - grocers like - they were shops and - anyway - Johnny said to me, you want to come and see me father. I said - all these things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 You told me what a lovely person your mother was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh she was a marvel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did she work in the mill as you children were growing up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No, she didn't work '}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2163708\charrsid6767433 till}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433  I was growing. No, she'd stopped working long before I went and was born. She was over forty when I was born. They'd been }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15881451 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433  twenty years. And the early part of the - the first three died. And - no, she didn't work when I - she was a little stout old lady - very stout. And eve
rybody loved her. And I think - and I think she loved everybody else. She didn't believe there were bad people I don't believe. She used to say - oh, - used to feel sorry for 'em - sorry for 'em. They went shooting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 This was your dad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 If they we
re in trouble - id she could help at all she was there. She was a wonderful won - wonderful old lady. And everybody thought so and this master of criminals as I call her - I - I don't know her name now, I - I must have now it then - I was astonished when 
she knew me name but - well, she gave orders to this school pal of mine that had become a criminal - he used to get locked up for the - steeling tie-pins - valuable tie-pins off gentlemen in town. And he was a bit of a confidence man like.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Only steal tie-pins - nothing else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Well I don't know about anything else but used to steal tie-pins. Well, they know who it was. He was a fool. It was simply go and pick Teddy Brown up and - he got five years - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8462345\charrsid6767433 those}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433  years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 He went to school with you did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Same time as me. And that was a strange thing. Their parents - they both worked - the father was an old shoemaker. The mother used to work in the - the - pork butchers that I tell you about - always helped in the family - there was rather big fam
ily - Bartons. She always helped there. They were both always working and they all went wrong. Teddy was a criminal - he never worked. Got in trouble very early. Then he went from bad to worse. He was always a criminal. His daughter - his sister told me t
hat he died with a - of T.B. but they killed him in prison. Now, that sister at one time was a bad case. She recovered. Chap off the railway }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15881451 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433  her. She had a family and two other sisters, one, Mary, not a bad girl at all Mary. She worked until she got
 tired of it. She was a - what they call a hooker in a warehouse. I don't know what it is but that's what she was - a hooker in a warehouse. The eldest sister had gone wrong early on. At the finish - Mary had a fall - she'd gone wrong early. A man from th
e market - in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Smithfield{\*\xmlclose} market }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15881451 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433  her and took took her to 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}America{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. I saw her later in life in a pub in Broughton with her mother - Kay - Jessie Xay. Oh, and she was loud mouthed. She recovered mind you - a lady but she was a bad youngster. But I met 
her pal Mary Brown - was a good girl, always worked. But Mary went - she got sick of it and - I lost sight of Mary. The - the mother and father worked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 You were saying conditions made this girl turn to prostitution - do you think the conditions in Gre
engate caused the boys to become criminals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I think her eldest sister was a natural - she was a high flier and went early. Then the next one that got pulled up and got }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15881451 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433  - she - no question she was doing it but a chap off the railway, named Mills, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15881451 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433  her and she turned out all - right like, had a family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Do you think it was conditions in Greengate that turned out so many criminals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well I suppose it was. But Mary Brown, she got sick of home conditions. Her mother didn't seem to h
ave any - home - they lived down an entry - it was - well it was - it was a passage - part of Frankenburg gathered that up. But - anyway Mary went wrong and I was always sorry for Mary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Do you think this is why the men became criminals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I told h
er, I said, oh I'm sorry to see this. Oh she said, Billy, I couldn't stand it any longer. She said, you're - I looked at her - she said, you're not mistaken - Mary all right. And she seemed quite resigned to it. Said what are you doing up here then? She s
aid, oh, I'm on a visit.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 You were telling me about someone you used to go to for help when you had trouble with the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Used to go to help when we had trouble with - when we had trouble with the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 If you were worried about the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Well I never had - was worried much - only our George. I used to have a talk to my sister and my brother when he was living but - my brother was very - he used to drink but he wasn't a bad sort of chap. He drank too much really but - he us
ed to work like and he had eight daughters and one son.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Was your mother alive when your children were small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Me mother was alive when the first child was born.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 How often did you see her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I never missed seeing me mother one day in me life when I was in Salford. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 You were very fond of her weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh, very fond of her. I used to call every day that I was in Salford as long as me mother lived I saw her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you ask her advice about bringing your children up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
No. No, I followed me own advice, I - I thought - I'm not conceited but I thought I had a fair view of life like - I had - I'd had a varied experience and seen a lot of different characters and - including the violent characters. I always told 'em to - w
ell, I had no need to tell 'em, they didn't have anything to do or - they despised that type of person. Even the betting chap. He'd no time for the violent rogue and the betting people - I knew people that was in the betting world - they said he was very 
honest fellow. Well that was nice to hear and he's a fool. They said he is. Said he wins a lot of money and then loses it. Right gambler.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did your mother have the same ideas about bringing children up as you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Who? My mother? My mother thought everybody was good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What about children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh she thought her children was the best. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did she have different ideas about bringing them up to what you did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No, no, she - as long as they went to church and at school and - as long as you went to church you was a very good boy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you think you should do the same with your children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well they went. I had no need to bother about them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What about your mother-in-law?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Never knew her. She was dead before I met my wife.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Can you tell me some of the things you felt you ought to do for your children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well - I'm sorry now that it's too late that I didn't give them a better education. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 They've done well thought haven't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 They've done marvelous.
 My daughter was in charge of forty shorthand typists at G.E.C. Some of them had been at Grammar until they were seventeen years or more and she left before she was thirteen and - had a little job - not much of a job - in some office before she went there
 
but she always wanted to work in the G.E.C. And - she was always determined to get on I think and very early - as a young person. She used to go when they made up the accounts at weekend and work for the boss. He - he was named Mr Farthing and - she used 
to be there and the - clerical part of the job helping them and she used to get four bob for this. Well that was her money and she thought she was well off.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What other things did you want for your children - what other things did you feel you ought to
 do for your children apart from giving them a good education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Well I wanted my son to be at a trade and - well I got - indirectly I got him at a trade. He went to Armstrong Whitworth first in a time office. Friend of mine got him the job but I didn'
t intend him to stop there and I - the man in the time office told him he said, you're wasting your time if you stop here. So he said, well I don't want to stop here in the office - my father wants me to go to a trade. Now in the same firm there was a man
 
that lived in our street - I don't know if he had any influence with my son getting to the bench but they closed Armstrong Whitworths when my son was seventeen and a half. And - he was in the middle of his apprenticeship. Now the foreman that he was under
, Mr. Belper, he was a foreman at Armstrongs and - he lived opposite to us, the foreman that he was under wanted to take him with him to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Leeds{\*\xmlclose}
. So Mr Barker had told my wife that the man he worked for was a rather tough character - he used to drink and swea
r and - good man, he thought the world of my son - best apprentice he ever had. So - when I heard this about them taking him with him I said, you're not going. I said, tell him you're not going. So, he told him and he said, oh I'll find you a job. So wher
e he is now - the man that was foreman then was a friend of his so he got him transferred from there to a - it was - what was the name of it - I just - I'll think of the name in a minute. It was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 How did you feel about affection with your children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Affectionate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 You said your dad wasn't affectionate and your mother was - how did you feel about this with your own children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh I - I - I liked them all right but I was never a fussing man. I didn't - I wasn't a - make a fuss of them kind o
f business. And I - I taught them not to depend on anybody else - to depend on themselves. Always try to depend on them - selves. Not accept for anything because they'd said so. To examine it and if they agreed with it all right - but if they didn't don't
 accept it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What about things like safety and food and discipline - what did you feel about these things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Food and discipline? Well I - I thought we did fairly well for our position. We had a tough time with Finnigans short time and that than - i
t was real thought I tell you until Leyland Motors and then they were growing up and I was getting a lot of money so I accumulated it - not too - not a lot but a fair amount. But my wife was ill three years and it went. I didn't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What were your ideas on discipline when you had your own children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
My ideas on discipline was that they must behave themselves - and if they did that's all I asked for. And they did. I never chastised them for nothing and - I had very - very little to say to them about chastising them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you worry about their safety or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Safety - no. No. My son had a friend and this friend had - I know that one part of his family wasn't too good and he used to tell rather alarming stories and - which I knew
 wasn't quite correct but - he joined the Navy eventually. But - they used to go dancing together and - I - I just warned him. I said don't accept what Alan said too seriously.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you like them to share their worries with you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No. I never - I 
didn't like them to be worried at all. I - we didn't worry them if we could help it but they used to worry for us. If things weren't going - they used to take our worries -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 If anything worried them did they come to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Nothing worried them - I 
tell you one thing that happened. When my son was about sixteen the boss - Mr Martin - one of the Martins - wanted to send him to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Birmingham{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 for six months in the motoring line and we were having a tough time. So when he told his mother she said don't tell
 your father 'cos he'll make you go and we can't do without your money. So I never knew. Well when I knew - said well, you've not been fair to him have you? She said, I couldn't manage, I couldn't manage as it was - I couldn't have managed at all without 
it. So that was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 How did you expect your children to behave towards you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Oh, they always behaved well towards us. Then I - I never asked 'em - to agree with me if they didn't agree. In encouraged them to tell me that - and they did do. Happe
n they'd something to tell me about like and - they never rebuked me for having a drink but they didn't think I was too good about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 When the children were young did you ever manage to leave them and get out together so that you could go out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Never went out and left them. Never left them. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you never have anyone to look after them for you while you went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No, never had anybody - we never left them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you let your children join in when grown ups were talking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh - let them - they didn't want letting, they joined in if they wanted to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What did you bring them up to consider important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well - progress for one thing - I always said they could move forward - I'd moved a bit forward from me father and
 they've moved a long way farther from me father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Anything else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No nothing else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Anything about being right and wrong?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you tell them they should hit back if someone hit - them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh yes. I - I - I always told the lads never let anybody hit you. That was my advice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Were there any children you discouraged them from playing with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No. I'd no need to stop them. They selected proper friends. Alan Collins is the only one that I knew part of his family wasn't just 
what I thought - I knew - perhaps he didn't know that they wasn't just the same, but I knew and I told my son I said, don't accept Alans - he was a bit of an alarmist like - dreamt a bit. And - I knew that too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 If your children did something you didn't like what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Well I - I - I never had to tell them of anything I didn't like. I - I didn't. I - I don't know that I ever - there was ever an occasion when there was anything I didn't like and my son he had a friend that died of T.B. - he
 used to - go and visit him and he made - I remember he made a - a bed table for him, like when he was a - lit - Jack - I'm trying to think - Jack Booth - Jack Booth, aye, that's right. His mother I think was a councillor. But Bill used to visit them unti
l late on.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Were they never punished at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I never struck one of them in my life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Suppose they did something that you thought was naughty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 They didn't do anything that was naughty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Nor for your wife either?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I don't think s
o. No, no. Only - no, they were very good children. They weren't - fops or soft or anything like that - they were just progressive and ambitious and industrious.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Would you say that your children received the ideas they had about how to behave from your wife or you or both of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Both of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 One didn't play a more important part than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
Only but - I'm giving my wife credit more than me. She spent a lot more time with them than me. And I'm giving my wife credit that she deserves. She spent a lot of time with them - never left them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 When your children had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well used to - used to get a few cakes or a bit of current bread or something - nothing very elaborate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did they have presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I don't know - I don't think we had money for presents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did they have friends in - guests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Odd times - odd ones - not much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Can you remember anything you did with your wife and children on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh Ch
ristmas - always tried to make a point of having a turkey on - Christmas Day. Yes, have done all my - did all my - my son and daughter does yet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What did you do for Christmas Day - how did you spend it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well - oh just kind of tea party. At Finnigans - the last two years that we had the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8462345\charrsid6767433 draw}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433  - they used to say that it was my draw - not the last two years - the year I was - before I was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15881451 Married}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433  and the year I was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15881451 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
 I won the first prize - turkey. And one of them was a twenty pound turkey - th
ere was enough for - my wife and me and me brother and his wife and me mother and father. Now me mother had a very big oven so we took it to me mother's and she cooked it there and then it was split up into three lots. That's how - that - one year went. A
nd then after I got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15881451 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433  I never won at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you have any musical instruments in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
That's a funny one. When - you remember when the kids had a ukelele - had ukeleles. Well Bill made a ukelele. And bent the wood - made it all right.
 He had it until he was grown up too. And when he hit it it was murder. He was an horrible musician - horrible musician. And - and when he tried to play it it was simply murder. Anyway he had that until - oh, he was getting on and then he gave it - give i
t one of his young cousins.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did any of you sing?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 My wife used to sing a bit but not much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you ever make music together as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 We wasn't - we wasn't a musical family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you play games with the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 My wife did but I didn't - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Were there books in your house when you were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15881451 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433  and the children were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Books? Not much. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What about newspapers or magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Oh newspapers - had magazines - newspapers - they all had to read until - well, I refused to read for me father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 When your children were growing up did you have books or newspapers or magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well - not to any extent. I - I never had a bookcase. No. I used to read a lot from the library. Oh, I was a member of the 
library until I couldn't go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What about your children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 
And do you know what my specialties was. Oh real intellectual. Detectives and cowboys. But I used to read other things as well but that was the two - it's only recent years that I don't go. And I could read a library book in a day comfortable.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you read aloud to your children or to each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Never. They wouldn't have listened to me anyway - they could read for themselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Were the children taken out visiting neighbours or friends or relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Not much. I used to take them out when I was a young. That was to show 'em off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Were they ever taken shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Shopping - no. Might take them for a few sweets. That's about all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did they go out with you on their own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 I told you - when me father used to take me out when he was - used to go on the beer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 But did you take your children out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No. No, I didn't take 'em out much. I used to take 'em out with the wife sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 But not on their own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 What did you do on Bank Holidays with the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Nothing particular.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you ever go away for a holiday as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Yes. Used to go to Blackpool - sometimes and it was - was {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Blackpool{\*\xmlclose}
 and - mostly I was away with the - volunteers. But we didn't go away a lot - we didn't went away - but not a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Did you go regularly every year or anything like that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 We hadn't - we hadn't enough money for holidays. For a lot of our lives there was no holiday money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 When you did go how long did you go for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 A week. Later in life -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Why did you go to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Blackpool{\*\xmlclose} particularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Well the children used to play on the sands and - I liked {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Blackpool{\*\xmlclose}
. I go yet. I - I don't go now but until a year or two ago I used to pick myself up and - I went one day last year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 When you went away on holiday did you all go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4413851 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15272546 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10761150\charrsid6767433 Can you tell me how you spent your Saturdays?
