ight. I heard him at St James's hall in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Oldfield Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 and - the - signing the pledge brought it - he was a grand looking old man. White her, big and - they were asking the audience - there was a batch of lus like - we wee anything but temperance although w
e were young. Batch of us. We went asking them to come along and sign the pledge. I was having none of that. That's what I wanted to tell you. General Booth in - in the Salvation Army.
